66  bool isThisCompleteObject(GlobalDecl GD) const override {
67  // The Microsoft ABI doesn't use separate complete-object vs.
68  // base-object variants of constructors, but it does of destructors.
69  if (isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(GD.getDecl())) {
70  switch (GD.getDtorType()) {
71  case Dtor_Complete:
72  case Dtor_Deleting:
73  return true;
74 
75  case Dtor_Base:
76  return false;
77 
78  case Dtor_Comdat: llvm_unreachable("emitting dtor comdat as function?");
79  }
80  llvm_unreachable("bad dtor kind");
81  }
82 
83  // No other kinds.
84  return false;
85  }

87  size_t getSrcArgforCopyCtor(const CXXConstructorDecl *CD,
88  FunctionArgList &Args) const override {
89  assert(Args.size() >= 2 &&
90  "expected the arglist to have at least two args!");
91  // The 'most_derived' parameter goes second if the ctor is variadic and
92  // has v-bases.
93  if (CD->getParent()->getNumVBases() > 0 &&
94  CD->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()->isVariadic())
95  return 2;
96  return 1;
97  }

99  std::vector<CharUnits> getVBPtrOffsets(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) override {
100  std::vector<CharUnits> VBPtrOffsets;
101  const ASTContext &Context = getContext();
102  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = Context.getASTRecordLayout(RD);
103 
104  const VBTableGlobals &VBGlobals = enumerateVBTables(RD);
105  for (const std::unique_ptr<VPtrInfo> &VBT : *VBGlobals.VBTables) {
106  const ASTRecordLayout &SubobjectLayout =
107  Context.getASTRecordLayout(VBT->IntroducingObject);
108  CharUnits Offs = VBT->NonVirtualOffset;
109  Offs += SubobjectLayout.getVBPtrOffset();
110  if (VBT->getVBaseWithVPtr())
111  Offs += Layout.getVBaseClassOffset(VBT->getVBaseWithVPtr());
112  VBPtrOffsets.push_back(Offs);
113  }
114  llvm::array_pod_sort(VBPtrOffsets.begin(), VBPtrOffsets.end());
115  return VBPtrOffsets;
116  }

198  // Background on MSVC destructors
199  // ==============================
200  //
201  // Both Itanium and MSVC ABIs have destructor variants. The variant names
202  // roughly correspond in the following way:
203  // Itanium Microsoft
204  // Base -> no name, just ~Class
205  // Complete -> vbase destructor
206  // Deleting -> scalar deleting destructor
207  // vector deleting destructor
208  //
209  // The base and complete destructors are the same as in Itanium, although the
210  // complete destructor does not accept a VTT parameter when there are virtual
211  // bases. A separate mechanism involving vtordisps is used to ensure that
212  // virtual methods of destroyed subobjects are not called.
213  //
214  // The deleting destructors accept an i32 bitfield as a second parameter. Bit
215  // 1 indicates if the memory should be deleted. Bit 2 indicates if the this
216  // pointer points to an array. The scalar deleting destructor assumes that
217  // bit 2 is zero, and therefore does not contain a loop.
218  //
219  // For virtual destructors, only one entry is reserved in the vftable, and it
220  // always points to the vector deleting destructor. The vector deleting
221  // destructor is the most general, so it can be used to destroy objects in
222  // place, delete single heap objects, or delete arrays.
223  //
224  // A TU defining a non-inline destructor is only guaranteed to emit a base
225  // destructor, and all of the other variants are emitted on an as-needed basis
226  // in COMDATs. Because a non-base destructor can be emitted in a TU that
227  // lacks a definition for the destructor, non-base destructors must always
228  // delegate to or alias the base destructor.

250  const CXXRecordDecl *getThisArgumentTypeForMethod(GlobalDecl GD) override {
251  auto *MD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(GD.getDecl());
252 
253  if (MD->isVirtual()) {
254  GlobalDecl LookupGD = GD;
255  if (const auto *DD = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD)) {
256  // Complete dtors take a pointer to the complete object,
257  // thus don't need adjustment.
258  if (GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Complete)
259  return MD->getParent();
260 
261  // There's only Dtor_Deleting in vftable but it shares the this
262  // adjustment with the base one, so look up the deleting one instead.
263  LookupGD = GlobalDecl(DD, Dtor_Deleting);
264  }
265  MethodVFTableLocation ML =
266  CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext().getMethodVFTableLocation(LookupGD);
267 
268  // The vbases might be ordered differently in the final overrider object
269  // and the complete object, so the "this" argument may sometimes point to
270  // memory that has no particular type (e.g. past the complete object).
271  // In this case, we just use a generic pointer type.
272  // FIXME: might want to have a more precise type in the non-virtual
273  // multiple inheritance case.
274  if (ML.VBase || !ML.VFPtrOffset.isZero())
275  return nullptr;
276  }
277  return MD->getParent();
278  }

356  llvm::GlobalVariable *
357  getAddrOfVirtualDisplacementMap(const CXXRecordDecl *SrcRD,
358  const CXXRecordDecl *DstRD) {
359  SmallString<256> OutName;
360  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(OutName);
361  getMangleContext().mangleCXXVirtualDisplacementMap(SrcRD, DstRD, Out);
362  StringRef MangledName = OutName.str();
363 
364  if (auto *VDispMap = CGM.getModule().getNamedGlobal(MangledName))
365  return VDispMap;
366 
367  MicrosoftVTableContext &VTContext = CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext();
368  unsigned NumEntries = 1 + SrcRD->getNumVBases();
369  SmallVector<llvm::Constant *, 4> Map(NumEntries,
370  llvm::UndefValue::get(CGM.IntTy));
371  Map[0] = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, 0);
372  bool AnyDifferent = false;
373  for (const auto &I : SrcRD->vbases()) {
374  const CXXRecordDecl *VBase = I.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
375  if (!DstRD->isVirtuallyDerivedFrom(VBase))
376  continue;
377 
378  unsigned SrcVBIndex = VTContext.getVBTableIndex(SrcRD, VBase);
379  unsigned DstVBIndex = VTContext.getVBTableIndex(DstRD, VBase);
380  Map[SrcVBIndex] = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, DstVBIndex * 4);
381  AnyDifferent |= SrcVBIndex != DstVBIndex;
382  }
383  // This map would be useless, don't use it.
384  if (!AnyDifferent)
385  return nullptr;
386 
387  llvm::ArrayType *VDispMapTy = llvm::ArrayType::get(CGM.IntTy, Map.size());
388  llvm::Constant *Init = llvm::ConstantArray::get(VDispMapTy, Map);
389  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage =
390  SrcRD->isExternallyVisible() && DstRD->isExternallyVisible()
391  ? llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage
392  : llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage;
393  auto *VDispMap = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
394  CGM.getModule(), VDispMapTy, /*isConstant=*/true, Linkage,
395  /*Initializer=*/Init, MangledName);
396  return VDispMap;
397  }

443  // ==== Notes on array cookies =========
444  //
445  // MSVC seems to only use cookies when the class has a destructor; a
446  // two-argument usual array deallocation function isn't sufficient.
447  //
448  // For example, this code prints "100" and "1":
449  // struct A {
450  // char x;
451  // void *operator new[](size_t sz) {
452  // printf("%u\n", sz);
453  // return malloc(sz);
454  // }
455  // void operator delete[](void *p, size_t sz) {
456  // printf("%u\n", sz);
457  // free(p);
458  // }
459  // };
460  // int main() {
461  // A *p = new A[100];
462  // delete[] p;
463  // }
464  // Whereas it prints "104" and "104" if you give A a destructor.
465

485  // 5 routines for constructing the llvm types for MS RTTI structs.
486  llvm::StructType *getTypeDescriptorType(StringRef TypeInfoString) {
487  llvm::SmallString<32> TDTypeName("rtti.TypeDescriptor");
488  TDTypeName += llvm::utostr(TypeInfoString.size());
489  llvm::StructType *&TypeDescriptorType =
490  TypeDescriptorTypeMap[TypeInfoString.size()];
491  if (TypeDescriptorType)
492  return TypeDescriptorType;
493  llvm::Type *FieldTypes[] = {
494  CGM.Int8PtrPtrTy,
495  CGM.Int8PtrTy,
496  llvm::ArrayType::get(CGM.Int8Ty, TypeInfoString.size() + 1)};
497  TypeDescriptorType =
498  llvm::StructType::create(CGM.getLLVMContext(), FieldTypes, TDTypeName);
499  return TypeDescriptorType;
500  }

575  llvm::Constant *getImageRelativeConstant(llvm::Constant *PtrVal) {
576  if (!isImageRelative())
577  return PtrVal;
578 
579  if (PtrVal->isNullValue())
580  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.IntTy);
581 
582  llvm::Constant *ImageBaseAsInt =
583  llvm::ConstantExpr::getPtrToInt(getImageBase(), CGM.IntPtrTy);
584  llvm::Constant *PtrValAsInt =
585  llvm::ConstantExpr::getPtrToInt(PtrVal, CGM.IntPtrTy);
586  llvm::Constant *Diff =
587  llvm::ConstantExpr::getSub(PtrValAsInt, ImageBaseAsInt,
588  /*HasNUW=*/true, /*HasNSW=*/true);
589  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getTrunc(Diff, CGM.IntTy);
590  }

852 CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI
853 MicrosoftCXXABI::getRecordArgABI(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) const {
854  // Use the default C calling convention rules for things that can be passed in
855  // registers, i.e. non-trivially copyable records or records marked with
856  // [[trivial_abi]].
857  if (RD->canPassInRegisters())
858  return RAA_Default;
859 
860  switch (CGM.getTarget().getTriple().getArch()) {
861  default:
862  // FIXME: Implement for other architectures.
863  return RAA_Indirect;
864 
865  case llvm::Triple::thumb:
866  // Pass things indirectly for now because it is simple.
867  // FIXME: This is incompatible with MSVC for arguments with a dtor and no
868  // copy ctor.
869  return RAA_Indirect;
870 
871  case llvm::Triple::x86: {
872  // If the argument has *required* alignment greater than four bytes, pass
873  // it indirectly. Prior to MSVC version 19.14, passing overaligned
874  // arguments was not supported and resulted in a compiler error. In 19.14
875  // and later versions, such arguments are now passed indirectly.
876  TypeInfo Info = getContext().getTypeInfo(RD->getTypeForDecl());
877  if (Info.isAlignRequired() && Info.Align > 4)
878  return RAA_Indirect;
879 
880  // If C++ prohibits us from making a copy, construct the arguments directly
881  // into argument memory.
882  return RAA_DirectInMemory;
883  }
884 
885  case llvm::Triple::x86_64:
886  case llvm::Triple::aarch64:
887  return RAA_Indirect;
888  }
889 
890  llvm_unreachable("invalid enum");
891 }

918 void MicrosoftCXXABI::emitBeginCatch(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
919  const CXXCatchStmt *S) {
920  // In the MS ABI, the runtime handles the copy, and the catch handler is
921  // responsible for destruction.
922  VarDecl *CatchParam = S->getExceptionDecl();
923  llvm::BasicBlock *CatchPadBB = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
924  llvm::CatchPadInst *CPI =
925  cast<llvm::CatchPadInst>(CatchPadBB->getFirstNonPHI());
926  CGF.CurrentFuncletPad = CPI;
927 
928  // If this is a catch-all or the catch parameter is unnamed, we don't need to
929  // emit an alloca to the object.
930  if (!CatchParam || !CatchParam->getDeclName()) {
931  CGF.EHStack.pushCleanup<CatchRetScope>(NormalCleanup, CPI);
932  return;
933  }
934 
935  CodeGenFunction::AutoVarEmission var = CGF.EmitAutoVarAlloca(*CatchParam);
936  CPI->setArgOperand(2, var.getObjectAddress(CGF).emitRawPointer(CGF));
937  CGF.EHStack.pushCleanup<CatchRetScope>(NormalCleanup, CPI);
938  CGF.EmitAutoVarCleanups(var);
939 }

941 /// We need to perform a generic polymorphic operation (like a typeid
942 /// or a cast), which requires an object with a vfptr. Adjust the
943 /// address to point to an object with a vfptr.
944 std::tuple<Address, llvm::Value *, const CXXRecordDecl *>
945 MicrosoftCXXABI::performBaseAdjustment(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address Value,
946  QualType SrcRecordTy) {
947  Value = Value.withElementType(CGF.Int8Ty);
948  const CXXRecordDecl *SrcDecl = SrcRecordTy->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
949  const ASTContext &Context = getContext();
950 
951  // If the class itself has a vfptr, great. This check implicitly
952  // covers non-virtual base subobjects: a class with its own virtual
953  // functions would be a candidate to be a primary base.
954  if (Context.getASTRecordLayout(SrcDecl).hasExtendableVFPtr())
955  return std::make_tuple(Value, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, 0),
956  SrcDecl);
957 
958  // Okay, one of the vbases must have a vfptr, or else this isn't
959  // actually a polymorphic class.
960  const CXXRecordDecl *PolymorphicBase = nullptr;
961  for (auto &Base : SrcDecl->vbases()) {
962  const CXXRecordDecl *BaseDecl = Base.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
963  if (Context.getASTRecordLayout(BaseDecl).hasExtendableVFPtr()) {
964  PolymorphicBase = BaseDecl;
965  break;
966  }
967  }
968  assert(PolymorphicBase && "polymorphic class has no apparent vfptr?");
969 
970  llvm::Value *Offset =
971  GetVirtualBaseClassOffset(CGF, Value, SrcDecl, PolymorphicBase);
972  llvm::Value *Ptr = CGF.Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(
973  Value.getElementType(), Value.emitRawPointer(CGF), Offset);
974  CharUnits VBaseAlign =
975  CGF.CGM.getVBaseAlignment(Value.getAlignment(), SrcDecl, PolymorphicBase);
976  return std::make_tuple(Address(Ptr, CGF.Int8Ty, VBaseAlign), Offset,
977  PolymorphicBase);
978 }

1073 llvm::Value *MicrosoftCXXABI::GetVirtualBaseClassOffset(
1074  CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address This, const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl,
1075  const CXXRecordDecl *BaseClassDecl) {

1107 static bool isTrivialForMSVC(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, QualType Ty,
1108  CodeGenModule &CGM) {
1109  // On AArch64, HVAs that can be passed in registers can also be returned
1110  // in registers. (Note this is using the MSVC definition of an HVA; see
1111  // isPermittedToBeHomogeneousAggregate().)
1112  const Type *Base = nullptr;
1113  uint64_t NumElts = 0;
1114  if (CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isAArch64() &&
1115  CGM.getTypes().getABIInfo().isHomogeneousAggregate(Ty, Base, NumElts) &&
1116  isa<VectorType>(Base)) {
1117  return true;
1118  }
1119 
1120  // We use the C++14 definition of an aggregate, so we also
1121  // check for:
1122  // No private or protected non static data members.
1123  // No base classes
1124  // No virtual functions
1125  // Additionally, we need to ensure that there is a trivial copy assignment
1126  // operator, a trivial destructor and no user-provided constructors.
1127  if (RD->hasProtectedFields() || RD->hasPrivateFields())
1128  return false;
1129  if (RD->getNumBases() > 0)
1130  return false;
1131  if (RD->isPolymorphic())
1132  return false;
1133  if (RD->hasNonTrivialCopyAssignment())
1134  return false;
1135  for (const CXXConstructorDecl *Ctor : RD->ctors())
1136  if (Ctor->isUserProvided())
1137  return false;
1138  if (RD->hasNonTrivialDestructor())
1139  return false;
1140  return true;
1141 }
1142 
1143 bool MicrosoftCXXABI::classifyReturnType(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
1144  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = FI.getReturnType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1145  if (!RD)
1146  return false;
1147 
1148  bool isTrivialForABI = RD->canPassInRegisters() &&
1149  isTrivialForMSVC(RD, FI.getReturnType(), CGM);
1150 
1151  // MSVC always returns structs indirectly from C++ instance methods.
1152  bool isIndirectReturn = !isTrivialForABI || FI.isInstanceMethod();
1153 
1154  if (isIndirectReturn) {
1155  CharUnits Align = CGM.getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(FI.getReturnType());
1156  FI.getReturnInfo() = ABIArgInfo::getIndirect(Align, /*ByVal=*/false);
1157 
1158  // MSVC always passes `this` before the `sret` parameter.
1159  FI.getReturnInfo().setSRetAfterThis(FI.isInstanceMethod());
1160 
1161  // On AArch64, use the `inreg` attribute if the object is considered to not
1162  // be trivially copyable, or if this is an instance method struct return.
1163  FI.getReturnInfo().setInReg(CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isAArch64());
1164 
1165  return true;
1166  }
1167 
1168  // Otherwise, use the C ABI rules.
1169  return false;
1170 }

1173 MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitCtorCompleteObjectHandler(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1174  const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {

1214 
1215 void MicrosoftCXXABI::initializeHiddenVirtualInheritanceMembers(
1216  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
1217  // In most cases, an override for a vbase virtual method can adjust
1218  // the "this" parameter by applying a constant offset.
1219  // However, this is not enough while a constructor or a destructor of some
1220  // class X is being executed if all the following conditions are met:
1221  // - X has virtual bases, (1)
1222  // - X overrides a virtual method M of a vbase Y, (2)
1223  // - X itself is a vbase of the most derived class.
1224  //
1225  // If (1) and (2) are true, the vtorDisp for vbase Y is a hidden member of X
1226  // which holds the extra amount of "this" adjustment we must do when we use
1227  // the X vftables (i.e. during X ctor or dtor).
1228  // Outside the ctors and dtors, the values of vtorDisps are zero.
1229 
1230  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
1231  typedef ASTRecordLayout::VBaseOffsetsMapTy VBOffsets;
1232  const VBOffsets &VBaseMap = Layout.getVBaseOffsetsMap();
1233  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
1234 
1235  llvm::Value *Int8This = nullptr; // Initialize lazily.
1236 
1237  for (const CXXBaseSpecifier &S : RD->vbases()) {
1238  const CXXRecordDecl *VBase = S.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1239  auto I = VBaseMap.find(VBase);
1240  assert(I != VBaseMap.end());
1241  if (!I->second.hasVtorDisp())
1242  continue;
1243 
1244  llvm::Value *VBaseOffset =
1245  GetVirtualBaseClassOffset(CGF, getThisAddress(CGF), RD, VBase);
1246  uint64_t ConstantVBaseOffset = I->second.VBaseOffset.getQuantity();
1247 
1248  // vtorDisp_for_vbase = vbptr[vbase_idx] - offsetof(RD, vbase).
1249  llvm::Value *VtorDispValue = Builder.CreateSub(
1250  VBaseOffset, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.PtrDiffTy, ConstantVBaseOffset),
1251  "vtordisp.value");
1252  VtorDispValue = Builder.CreateTruncOrBitCast(VtorDispValue, CGF.Int32Ty);
1253 
1254  if (!Int8This)
1255  Int8This = getThisValue(CGF);
1256 
1257  llvm::Value *VtorDispPtr =
1258  Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, Int8This, VBaseOffset);
1259  // vtorDisp is always the 32-bits before the vbase in the class layout.
1260  VtorDispPtr = Builder.CreateConstGEP1_32(CGF.Int8Ty, VtorDispPtr, -4);
1261 
1262  Builder.CreateAlignedStore(VtorDispValue, VtorDispPtr,
1263  CharUnits::fromQuantity(4));
1264  }
1265 }

1267 static bool hasDefaultCXXMethodCC(ASTContext &Context,
1268  const CXXMethodDecl *MD) {
1269  CallingConv ExpectedCallingConv = Context.getDefaultCallingConvention(
1270  /*IsVariadic=*/false, /*IsCXXMethod=*/true);
1271  CallingConv ActualCallingConv =
1272  MD->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()->getCallConv();
1273  return ExpectedCallingConv == ActualCallingConv;
1274 }

1276 void MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitCXXConstructors(const CXXConstructorDecl *D) {
1277  // There's only one constructor type in this ABI.
1278  CGM.EmitGlobal(GlobalDecl(D, Ctor_Complete));
1279 
1280  // Exported default constructors either have a simple call-site where they use
1281  // the typical calling convention and have a single 'this' pointer for an
1282  // argument -or- they get a wrapper function which appropriately thunks to the
1283  // real default constructor. This thunk is the default constructor closure.
1284  if (D->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>() && D->isDefaultConstructor() &&
1285  D->isDefined()) {
1286  if (!hasDefaultCXXMethodCC(getContext(), D) || D->getNumParams() != 0) {
1287  llvm::Function *Fn = getAddrOfCXXCtorClosure(D, Ctor_DefaultClosure);

1289  CGM.setGVProperties(Fn, D);
1290  }
1291  }

1294 void MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitVBPtrStores(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1295  const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
1296  Address This = getThisAddress(CGF);
1297  This = This.withElementType(CGM.Int8Ty);
1298  const ASTContext &Context = getContext();
1299  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = Context.getASTRecordLayout(RD);
1300 
1301  const VBTableGlobals &VBGlobals = enumerateVBTables(RD);
1302  for (unsigned I = 0, E = VBGlobals.VBTables->size(); I != E; ++I) {
1303  const std::unique_ptr<VPtrInfo> &VBT = (*VBGlobals.VBTables)[I];
1304  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = VBGlobals.Globals[I];
1305  const ASTRecordLayout &SubobjectLayout =
1306  Context.getASTRecordLayout(VBT->IntroducingObject);
1307  CharUnits Offs = VBT->NonVirtualOffset;
1308  Offs += SubobjectLayout.getVBPtrOffset();
1309  if (VBT->getVBaseWithVPtr())
1310  Offs += Layout.getVBaseClassOffset(VBT->getVBaseWithVPtr());
1311  Address VBPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(This, Offs);
1312  llvm::Value *GVPtr =
1313  CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP2_32(GV->getValueType(), GV, 0, 0);
1314  VBPtr = VBPtr.withElementType(GVPtr->getType());
1315  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(GVPtr, VBPtr);
1316  }
1317 }

1319 CGCXXABI::AddedStructorArgCounts
1320 MicrosoftCXXABI::buildStructorSignature(GlobalDecl GD,
1321  SmallVectorImpl<CanQualType> &ArgTys) {
1322  AddedStructorArgCounts Added;
1323  // TODO: 'for base' flag
1324  if (isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(GD.getDecl()) &&
1325  GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Deleting) {
1326  // The scalar deleting destructor takes an implicit int parameter.
1327  ArgTys.push_back(getContext().IntTy);
1328  ++Added.Suffix;
1329  }
1330  auto *CD = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(GD.getDecl());
1331  if (!CD)
1332  return Added;
1333 
1334  // All parameters are already in place except is_most_derived, which goes
1335  // after 'this' if it's variadic and last if it's not.
1336 
1337  const CXXRecordDecl *Class = CD->getParent();
1338  const FunctionProtoType *FPT = CD->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
1339  if (Class->getNumVBases()) {
1340  if (FPT->isVariadic()) {
1341  ArgTys.insert(ArgTys.begin() + 1, getContext().IntTy);
1342  ++Added.Prefix;
1343  } else {
1344  ArgTys.push_back(getContext().IntTy);
1345  ++Added.Suffix;
1346  }
1347  }
1348 
1349  return Added;
1350 }

1364 
1365 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes MicrosoftCXXABI::getCXXDestructorLinkage(
1366  GVALinkage Linkage, const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor, CXXDtorType DT) const {
1367  // Internal things are always internal, regardless of attributes. After this,
1368  // we know the thunk is externally visible.
1369  if (Linkage == GVA_Internal)
1370  return llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage;
1371 
1372  switch (DT) {
1373  case Dtor_Base:
1374  // The base destructor most closely tracks the user-declared constructor, so
1375  // we delegate back to the normal declarator case.
1376  return CGM.getLLVMLinkageForDeclarator(Dtor, Linkage);
1377  case Dtor_Complete:
1378  // The complete destructor is like an inline function, but it may be
1379  // imported and therefore must be exported as well. This requires changing
1380  // the linkage if a DLL attribute is present.
1381  if (Dtor->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())
1382  return llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage;
1383  if (Dtor->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
1384  return llvm::GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage;
1385  return llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage;
1386  case Dtor_Deleting:
1387  // Deleting destructors are like inline functions. They have vague linkage
1388  // and are emitted everywhere they are used. They are internal if the class
1389  // is internal.
1390  return llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage;
1391  case Dtor_Comdat:
1392  llvm_unreachable("MS C++ ABI does not support comdat dtors");
1393  }
1394  llvm_unreachable("invalid dtor type");
1395 }

1397 void MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitCXXDestructors(const CXXDestructorDecl *D) {
1398  // The TU defining a dtor is only guaranteed to emit a base destructor. All
1399  // other destructor variants are delegating thunks.
1400  CGM.EmitGlobal(GlobalDecl(D, Dtor_Base));
1401 
1402  // If the class is dllexported, emit the complete (vbase) destructor wherever
1403  // the base dtor is emitted.
1404  // FIXME: To match MSVC, this should only be done when the class is exported
1405  // with -fdllexport-inlines enabled.
1406  if (D->getParent()->getNumVBases() > 0 && D->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())
1407  CGM.EmitGlobal(GlobalDecl(D, Dtor_Complete));
1408 }

1410 CharUnits
1411 MicrosoftCXXABI::getVirtualFunctionPrologueThisAdjustment(GlobalDecl GD) {
1412  const CXXMethodDecl *MD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(GD.getDecl());
1413 
1414  if (const CXXDestructorDecl *DD = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD)) {
1415  // Complete destructors take a pointer to the complete object as a
1416  // parameter, thus don't need this adjustment.
1417  if (GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Complete)
1418  return CharUnits();
1419 
1420  // There's no Dtor_Base in vftable but it shares the this adjustment with
1421  // the deleting one, so look it up instead.
1422  GD = GlobalDecl(DD, Dtor_Deleting);
1423  }
1424 
1425  MethodVFTableLocation ML =
1426  CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext().getMethodVFTableLocation(GD);
1427  CharUnits Adjustment = ML.VFPtrOffset;
1428 
1429  // Normal virtual instance methods need to adjust from the vfptr that first
1430  // defined the virtual method to the virtual base subobject, but destructors
1431  // do not. The vector deleting destructor thunk applies this adjustment for
1432  // us if necessary.
1433  if (isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD))
1434  Adjustment = CharUnits::Zero();
1435 
1436  if (ML.VBase) {
1437  const ASTRecordLayout &DerivedLayout =
1438  getContext().getASTRecordLayout(MD->getParent());
1439  Adjustment += DerivedLayout.getVBaseClassOffset(ML.VBase);
1440  }
1441 
1442  return Adjustment;
1443 }
1444 
1445 Address MicrosoftCXXABI::adjustThisArgumentForVirtualFunctionCall(
1446  CodeGenFunction &CGF, GlobalDecl GD, Address This,
1447  bool VirtualCall) {
1448  if (!VirtualCall) {
1449  // If the call of a virtual function is not virtual, we just have to
1450  // compensate for the adjustment the virtual function does in its prologue.
1451  CharUnits Adjustment = getVirtualFunctionPrologueThisAdjustment(GD);
1452  if (Adjustment.isZero())
1453  return This;
1454 
1455  This = This.withElementType(CGF.Int8Ty);
1456  assert(Adjustment.isPositive());
1457  return CGF.Builder.CreateConstByteGEP(This, Adjustment);
1458  }
1459 
1460  const CXXMethodDecl *MD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(GD.getDecl());
1461 
1462  GlobalDecl LookupGD = GD;
1463  if (const CXXDestructorDecl *DD = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD)) {
1464  // Complete dtors take a pointer to the complete object,
1465  // thus don't need adjustment.
1466  if (GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Complete)
1467  return This;
1468 
1469  // There's only Dtor_Deleting in vftable but it shares the this adjustment
1470  // with the base one, so look up the deleting one instead.
1471  LookupGD = GlobalDecl(DD, Dtor_Deleting);
1472  }
1473  MethodVFTableLocation ML =
1474  CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext().getMethodVFTableLocation(LookupGD);
1475 
1476  CharUnits StaticOffset = ML.VFPtrOffset;
1477 
1478  // Base destructors expect 'this' to point to the beginning of the base
1479  // subobject, not the first vfptr that happens to contain the virtual dtor.
1480  // However, we still need to apply the virtual base adjustment.
1481  if (isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD) && GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Base)
1482  StaticOffset = CharUnits::Zero();
1483 
1484  Address Result = This;
1485  if (ML.VBase) {
1486  Result = Result.withElementType(CGF.Int8Ty);
1487 
1488  const CXXRecordDecl *Derived = MD->getParent();
1489  const CXXRecordDecl *VBase = ML.VBase;
1490  llvm::Value *VBaseOffset =
1491  GetVirtualBaseClassOffset(CGF, Result, Derived, VBase);
1492  llvm::Value *VBasePtr = CGF.Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(
1493  Result.getElementType(), Result.emitRawPointer(CGF), VBaseOffset);
1494  CharUnits VBaseAlign =
1495  CGF.CGM.getVBaseAlignment(Result.getAlignment(), Derived, VBase);
1496  Result = Address(VBasePtr, CGF.Int8Ty, VBaseAlign);
1497  }
1498  if (!StaticOffset.isZero()) {
1499  assert(StaticOffset.isPositive());
1500  Result = Result.withElementType(CGF.Int8Ty);
1501  if (ML.VBase) {
1502  // Non-virtual adjustment might result in a pointer outside the allocated
1503  // object, e.g. if the final overrider class is laid out after the virtual
1504  // base that declares a method in the most derived class.
1505  // FIXME: Update the code that emits this adjustment in thunks prologues.
1506  Result = CGF.Builder.CreateConstByteGEP(Result, StaticOffset);
1507  } else {
1508  Result = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(Result, StaticOffset);
1509  }
1510  }
1511  return Result;
1512 }

1514 void MicrosoftCXXABI::addImplicitStructorParams(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1515  QualType &ResTy,
1516  FunctionArgList &Params) {
1517  ASTContext &Context = getContext();
1518  const CXXMethodDecl *MD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CGF.CurGD.getDecl());
1519  assert(isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD) || isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD));
1520  if (isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD) && MD->getParent()->getNumVBases()) {
1521  auto *IsMostDerived = ImplicitParamDecl::Create(
1522  Context, /*DC=*/nullptr, CGF.CurGD.getDecl()->getLocation(),
1523  &Context.Idents.get("is_most_derived"), Context.IntTy,
1524  ImplicitParamKind::Other);
1525  // The 'most_derived' parameter goes second if the ctor is variadic and last
1526  // if it's not. Dtors can't be variadic.
1527  const FunctionProtoType *FPT = MD->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
1528  if (FPT->isVariadic())
1529  Params.insert(Params.begin() + 1, IsMostDerived);
1530  else
1531  Params.push_back(IsMostDerived);
1532  getStructorImplicitParamDecl(CGF) = IsMostDerived;
1533  } else if (isDeletingDtor(CGF.CurGD)) {
1534  auto *ShouldDelete = ImplicitParamDecl::Create(
1535  Context, /*DC=*/nullptr, CGF.CurGD.getDecl()->getLocation(),
1536  &Context.Idents.get("should_call_delete"), Context.IntTy,
1537  ImplicitParamKind::Other);
1538  Params.push_back(ShouldDelete);
1539  getStructorImplicitParamDecl(CGF) = ShouldDelete;
1540  }
1541 }
1542 
1543 void MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitInstanceFunctionProlog(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1544  // Naked functions have no prolog.
1545  if (CGF.CurFuncDecl && CGF.CurFuncDecl->hasAttr<NakedAttr>())
1546  return;
1547 
1548  // Overridden virtual methods of non-primary bases need to adjust the incoming
1549  // 'this' pointer in the prologue. In this hierarchy, C::b will subtract
1550  // sizeof(void*) to adjust from B* to C*:
1551  // struct A { virtual void a(); };
1552  // struct B { virtual void b(); };
1553  // struct C : A, B { virtual void b(); };
1554  //
1555  // Leave the value stored in the 'this' alloca unadjusted, so that the
1556  // debugger sees the unadjusted value. Microsoft debuggers require this, and
1557  // will apply the ThisAdjustment in the method type information.
1558  // FIXME: Do something better for DWARF debuggers, which won't expect this,
1559  // without making our codegen depend on debug info settings.
1560  llvm::Value *This = loadIncomingCXXThis(CGF);
1561  const CXXMethodDecl *MD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CGF.CurGD.getDecl());
1562  if (!CGF.CurFuncIsThunk && MD->isVirtual()) {
1563  CharUnits Adjustment = getVirtualFunctionPrologueThisAdjustment(CGF.CurGD);
1564  if (!Adjustment.isZero()) {
1565  assert(Adjustment.isPositive());
1566  This = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_32(CGF.Int8Ty, This,
1567  -Adjustment.getQuantity());
1568  }
1569  }
1570  setCXXABIThisValue(CGF, This);
1571 
1572  // If this is a function that the ABI specifies returns 'this', initialize
1573  // the return slot to 'this' at the start of the function.
1574  //
1575  // Unlike the setting of return types, this is done within the ABI
1576  // implementation instead of by clients of CGCXXABI because:
1577  // 1) getThisValue is currently protected
1578  // 2) in theory, an ABI could implement 'this' returns some other way;
1579  // HasThisReturn only specifies a contract, not the implementation
1580  if (HasThisReturn(CGF.CurGD) || hasMostDerivedReturn(CGF.CurGD))
1581  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(getThisValue(CGF), CGF.ReturnValue);
1582 
1583  if (isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD) && MD->getParent()->getNumVBases()) {
1584  assert(getStructorImplicitParamDecl(CGF) &&
1585  "no implicit parameter for a constructor with virtual bases?");
1586  getStructorImplicitParamValue(CGF)
1587  = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(
1588  CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(getStructorImplicitParamDecl(CGF)),
1589  "is_most_derived");
1590  }
1591 
1592  if (isDeletingDtor(CGF.CurGD)) {
1593  assert(getStructorImplicitParamDecl(CGF) &&
1594  "no implicit parameter for a deleting destructor?");
1595  getStructorImplicitParamValue(CGF)
1596  = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(
1597  CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(getStructorImplicitParamDecl(CGF)),
1598  "should_call_delete");
1599  }
1600 }

1602 CGCXXABI::AddedStructorArgs MicrosoftCXXABI::getImplicitConstructorArgs(
1603  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXConstructorDecl *D, CXXCtorType Type,
1604  bool ForVirtualBase, bool Delegating) {
1605  assert(Type == Ctor_Complete || Type == Ctor_Base);
1606 
1607  // Check if we need a 'most_derived' parameter.
1608  if (!D->getParent()->getNumVBases())
1609  return AddedStructorArgs{};
1610 
1611  // Add the 'most_derived' argument second if we are variadic or last if not.
1612  const FunctionProtoType *FPT = D->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
1613  llvm::Value *MostDerivedArg;
1614  if (Delegating) {
1615  MostDerivedArg = getStructorImplicitParamValue(CGF);
1616  } else {
1617  MostDerivedArg = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, Type == Ctor_Complete);
1618  }
1619  if (FPT->isVariadic()) {
1620  return AddedStructorArgs::prefix({{MostDerivedArg, getContext().IntTy}});
1621  }
1622  return AddedStructorArgs::suffix({{MostDerivedArg, getContext().IntTy}});
1623 }

1630 
1631 void MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitDestructorCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1632  const CXXDestructorDecl *DD,
1633  CXXDtorType Type, bool ForVirtualBase,
1634  bool Delegating, Address This,
1635  QualType ThisTy) {
1636  // Use the base destructor variant in place of the complete destructor variant
1637  // if the class has no virtual bases. This effectively implements some of the
1638  // -mconstructor-aliases optimization, but as part of the MS C++ ABI.
1639  if (Type == Dtor_Complete && DD->getParent()->getNumVBases() == 0)
1640  Type = Dtor_Base;
1641 
1642  GlobalDecl GD(DD, Type);
1643  CGCallee Callee = CGCallee::forDirect(CGM.getAddrOfCXXStructor(GD), GD);
1644 
1645  if (DD->isVirtual()) {
1646  assert(Type != CXXDtorType::Dtor_Deleting &&
1647  "The deleting destructor should only be called via a virtual call");
1648  This = adjustThisArgumentForVirtualFunctionCall(CGF, GlobalDecl(DD, Type),
1649  This, false);
1650  }
1651 
1652  llvm::BasicBlock *BaseDtorEndBB = nullptr;
1653  if (ForVirtualBase && isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(CGF.CurCodeDecl)) {
1654  BaseDtorEndBB = EmitDtorCompleteObjectHandler(CGF);
1655  }
1656 
1657  llvm::Value *Implicit =
1658  getCXXDestructorImplicitParam(CGF, DD, Type, ForVirtualBase,
1659  Delegating); // = nullptr
1660  CGF.EmitCXXDestructorCall(GD, Callee, CGF.getAsNaturalPointerTo(This, ThisTy),
1661  ThisTy,
1662  /*ImplicitParam=*/Implicit,
1663  /*ImplicitParamTy=*/QualType(), nullptr);
1664  if (BaseDtorEndBB) {
1665  // Complete object handler should continue to be the remaining
1666  CGF.Builder.CreateBr(BaseDtorEndBB);
1667  CGF.EmitBlock(BaseDtorEndBB);
1668  }
1669 }
1670 
1671 void MicrosoftCXXABI::emitVTableTypeMetadata(const VPtrInfo &Info,
1672  const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
1673  llvm::GlobalVariable *VTable) {
1674  // Emit type metadata on vtables with LTO or IR instrumentation.
1675  // In IR instrumentation, the type metadata could be used to find out vtable
1676  // definitions (for type profiling) among all global variables.
1677  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().LTOUnit &&
1678  !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasProfileIRInstr())
1679  return;
1680 
1681  // TODO: Should VirtualFunctionElimination also be supported here?
1682  // See similar handling in CodeGenModule::EmitVTableTypeMetadata.
1683  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().WholeProgramVTables) {
1684  llvm::DenseSet<const CXXRecordDecl *> Visited;
1685  llvm::GlobalObject::VCallVisibility TypeVis =
1686  CGM.GetVCallVisibilityLevel(RD, Visited);
1687  if (TypeVis != llvm::GlobalObject::VCallVisibilityPublic)
1688  VTable->setVCallVisibilityMetadata(TypeVis);
1689  }
1690 
1691  // The location of the first virtual function pointer in the virtual table,
1692  // aka the "address point" on Itanium. This is at offset 0 if RTTI is
1693  // disabled, or sizeof(void*) if RTTI is enabled.
1694  CharUnits AddressPoint =
1695  getContext().getLangOpts().RTTIData
1696  ? getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(
1697  getContext().getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(LangAS::Default))
1698  : CharUnits::Zero();
1699 
1700  if (Info.PathToIntroducingObject.empty()) {
1701  CGM.AddVTableTypeMetadata(VTable, AddressPoint, RD);
1702  return;
1703  }
1704 
1705  // Add a bitset entry for the least derived base belonging to this vftable.
1706  CGM.AddVTableTypeMetadata(VTable, AddressPoint,
1707  Info.PathToIntroducingObject.back());
1708 
1709  // Add a bitset entry for each derived class that is laid out at the same
1710  // offset as the least derived base.
1711  for (unsigned I = Info.PathToIntroducingObject.size() - 1; I != 0; --I) {
1712  const CXXRecordDecl *DerivedRD = Info.PathToIntroducingObject[I - 1];
1713  const CXXRecordDecl *BaseRD = Info.PathToIntroducingObject[I];
1714 
1715  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout =
1716  getContext().getASTRecordLayout(DerivedRD);
1717  CharUnits Offset;
1718  auto VBI = Layout.getVBaseOffsetsMap().find(BaseRD);
1719  if (VBI == Layout.getVBaseOffsetsMap().end())
1720  Offset = Layout.getBaseClassOffset(BaseRD);
1721  else
1722  Offset = VBI->second.VBaseOffset;
1723  if (!Offset.isZero())
1724  return;
1725  CGM.AddVTableTypeMetadata(VTable, AddressPoint, DerivedRD);
1726  }
1727 
1728  // Finally do the same for the most derived class.
1729  if (Info.FullOffsetInMDC.isZero())
1730  CGM.AddVTableTypeMetadata(VTable, AddressPoint, RD);
1731 }
1732 
1733 void MicrosoftCXXABI::emitVTableDefinitions(CodeGenVTables &CGVT,
1734  const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
1735  MicrosoftVTableContext &VFTContext = CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext();
1736  const VPtrInfoVector &VFPtrs = VFTContext.getVFPtrOffsets(RD);
1737 
1738  for (const std::unique_ptr<VPtrInfo>& Info : VFPtrs) {
1739  llvm::GlobalVariable *VTable = getAddrOfVTable(RD, Info->FullOffsetInMDC);
1740  if (VTable->hasInitializer())
1741  continue;
1742 
1743  const VTableLayout &VTLayout =
1744  VFTContext.getVFTableLayout(RD, Info->FullOffsetInMDC);
1745 
1746  llvm::Constant *RTTI = nullptr;
1747  if (any_of(VTLayout.vtable_components(),
1748  [](const VTableComponent &VTC) { return VTC.isRTTIKind(); }))
1749  RTTI = getMSCompleteObjectLocator(RD, *Info);
1750 
1751  ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
1752  auto components = builder.beginStruct();
1753  CGVT.createVTableInitializer(components, VTLayout, RTTI,
1754  VTable->hasLocalLinkage());
1755  components.finishAndSetAsInitializer(VTable);
1756 
1757  emitVTableTypeMetadata(*Info, RD, VTable);
1758  }
1759 }

1792 llvm::GlobalVariable *MicrosoftCXXABI::getAddrOfVTable(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
1793  CharUnits VPtrOffset) {
1794  // getAddrOfVTable may return 0 if asked to get an address of a vtable which
1795  // shouldn't be used in the given record type. We want to cache this result in
1796  // VFTablesMap, thus a simple zero check is not sufficient.
1797 
1798  VFTableIdTy ID(RD, VPtrOffset);
1799  VTablesMapTy::iterator I;
1800  bool Inserted;
1801  std::tie(I, Inserted) = VTablesMap.insert(std::make_pair(ID, nullptr));
1802  if (!Inserted)
1803  return I->second;
1804 
1805  llvm::GlobalVariable *&VTable = I->second;
1806 
1807  MicrosoftVTableContext &VTContext = CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext();
1808  const VPtrInfoVector &VFPtrs = VTContext.getVFPtrOffsets(RD);
1809 
1810  if (DeferredVFTables.insert(RD).second) {
1811  // We haven't processed this record type before.
1812  // Queue up this vtable for possible deferred emission.
1813  CGM.addDeferredVTable(RD);
1814 
1815 #ifndef NDEBUG
1816  // Create all the vftables at once in order to make sure each vftable has
1817  // a unique mangled name.
1818  llvm::StringSet<> ObservedMangledNames;
1819  for (size_t J = 0, F = VFPtrs.size(); J != F; ++J) {
1820  SmallString<256> Name;
1821  mangleVFTableName(getMangleContext(), RD, *VFPtrs[J], Name);
1822  if (!ObservedMangledNames.insert(Name.str()).second)
1823  llvm_unreachable("Already saw this mangling before?");
1824  }
1825 #endif
1826  }
1827 
1828  const std::unique_ptr<VPtrInfo> *VFPtrI =
1829  llvm::find_if(VFPtrs, [&](const std::unique_ptr<VPtrInfo> &VPI) {
1830  return VPI->FullOffsetInMDC == VPtrOffset;
1831  });
1832  if (VFPtrI == VFPtrs.end()) {
1833  VFTablesMap[ID] = nullptr;
1834  return nullptr;
1835  }
1836  const std::unique_ptr<VPtrInfo> &VFPtr = *VFPtrI;
1837 
1838  SmallString<256> VFTableName;
1839  mangleVFTableName(getMangleContext(), RD, *VFPtr, VFTableName);
1840 
1841  // Classes marked __declspec(dllimport) need vftables generated on the
1842  // import-side in order to support features like constexpr. No other
1843  // translation unit relies on the emission of the local vftable, translation
1844  // units are expected to generate them as needed.
1845  //
1846  // Because of this unique behavior, we maintain this logic here instead of
1847  // getVTableLinkage.
1848  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes VFTableLinkage =
1849  RD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>() ? llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage
1850  : CGM.getVTableLinkage(RD);
1851  bool VFTableComesFromAnotherTU =
1852  llvm::GlobalValue::isAvailableExternallyLinkage(VFTableLinkage) ||
1853  llvm::GlobalValue::isExternalLinkage(VFTableLinkage);
1854  bool VTableAliasIsRequred =
1855  !VFTableComesFromAnotherTU && getContext().getLangOpts().RTTIData;
1856 
1857  if (llvm::GlobalValue *VFTable =
1858  CGM.getModule().getNamedGlobal(VFTableName)) {
1859  VFTablesMap[ID] = VFTable;
1860  VTable = VTableAliasIsRequred
1861  ? cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(
1862  cast<llvm::GlobalAlias>(VFTable)->getAliaseeObject())
1863  : cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(VFTable);
1864  return VTable;
1865  }
1866 
1867  const VTableLayout &VTLayout =
1868  VTContext.getVFTableLayout(RD, VFPtr->FullOffsetInMDC);
1869  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes VTableLinkage =
1870  VTableAliasIsRequred ? llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage : VFTableLinkage;
1871 
1872  StringRef VTableName = VTableAliasIsRequred ? StringRef() : VFTableName.str();
1873 
1874  llvm::Type *VTableType = CGM.getVTables().getVTableType(VTLayout);
1875 
1876  // Create a backing variable for the contents of VTable. The VTable may
1877  // or may not include space for a pointer to RTTI data.
1878  llvm::GlobalValue *VFTable;
1879  VTable = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), VTableType,
1880  /*isConstant=*/true, VTableLinkage,
1881  /*Initializer=*/nullptr, VTableName);
1882  VTable->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
1883 
1884  llvm::Comdat *C = nullptr;
1885  if (!VFTableComesFromAnotherTU &&
1886  llvm::GlobalValue::isWeakForLinker(VFTableLinkage))
1887  C = CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(VFTableName.str());
1888 
1889  // Only insert a pointer into the VFTable for RTTI data if we are not
1890  // importing it. We never reference the RTTI data directly so there is no
1891  // need to make room for it.
1892  if (VTableAliasIsRequred) {
1893  llvm::Value *GEPIndices[] = {llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, 0),
1894  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, 0),
1895  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, 1)};
1896  // Create a GEP which points just after the first entry in the VFTable,
1897  // this should be the location of the first virtual method.
1898  llvm::Constant *VTableGEP = llvm::ConstantExpr::getInBoundsGetElementPtr(
1899  VTable->getValueType(), VTable, GEPIndices);
1900  if (llvm::GlobalValue::isWeakForLinker(VFTableLinkage)) {
1901  VFTableLinkage = llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage;
1902  if (C)
1903  C->setSelectionKind(llvm::Comdat::Largest);
1904  }
1905  VFTable = llvm::GlobalAlias::create(CGM.Int8PtrTy,
1906  /*AddressSpace=*/0, VFTableLinkage,
1907  VFTableName.str(), VTableGEP,
1908  &CGM.getModule());
1909  VFTable->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
1910  } else {
1911  // We don't need a GlobalAlias to be a symbol for the VTable if we won't
1912  // be referencing any RTTI data.
1913  // The GlobalVariable will end up being an appropriate definition of the
1914  // VFTable.
1915  VFTable = VTable;
1916  }
1917  if (C)
1918  VTable->setComdat(C);
1919 
1920  if (RD->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())
1921  VFTable->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLExportStorageClass);
1922 
1923  VFTablesMap[ID] = VFTable;
1924  return VTable;
1925 }
1926 
1927 CGCallee MicrosoftCXXABI::getVirtualFunctionPointer(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1928  GlobalDecl GD,
1929  Address This,
1930  llvm::Type *Ty,
1931  SourceLocation Loc) {
1932  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
1933 
1934  Ty = Ty->getPointerTo();
1935  Address VPtr =
1936  adjustThisArgumentForVirtualFunctionCall(CGF, GD, This, true);
1937 
1938  auto *MethodDecl = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(GD.getDecl());
1939  llvm::Value *VTable = CGF.GetVTablePtr(VPtr, Ty->getPointerTo(),
1940  MethodDecl->getParent());
1941 
1942  MicrosoftVTableContext &VFTContext = CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext();
1943  MethodVFTableLocation ML = VFTContext.getMethodVFTableLocation(GD);
1944 
1945  // Compute the identity of the most derived class whose virtual table is
1946  // located at the MethodVFTableLocation ML.
1947  auto getObjectWithVPtr = [&] {
1948  return llvm::find_if(VFTContext.getVFPtrOffsets(
1949  ML.VBase ? ML.VBase : MethodDecl->getParent()),
1950  [&](const std::unique_ptr<VPtrInfo> &Info) {
1951  return Info->FullOffsetInMDC == ML.VFPtrOffset;
1952  })
1953  ->get()
1954  ->ObjectWithVPtr;
1955  };
1956 
1957  llvm::Value *VFunc;
1958  if (CGF.ShouldEmitVTableTypeCheckedLoad(MethodDecl->getParent())) {
1959  VFunc = CGF.EmitVTableTypeCheckedLoad(
1960  getObjectWithVPtr(), VTable, Ty,
1961  ML.Index *
1962  CGM.getContext().getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(LangAS::Default) /
1963  8);
1964  } else {
1965  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().PrepareForLTO)
1966  CGF.EmitTypeMetadataCodeForVCall(getObjectWithVPtr(), VTable, Loc);
1967 
1968  llvm::Value *VFuncPtr =
1969  Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(Ty, VTable, ML.Index, "vfn");
1970  VFunc = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(Ty, VFuncPtr, CGF.getPointerAlign());
1971  }
1972 
1973  CGCallee Callee(GD, VFunc);
1974  return Callee;
1975 }

1977 llvm::Value *MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitVirtualDestructorCall(
1978  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor, CXXDtorType DtorType,
1979  Address This, DeleteOrMemberCallExpr E) {
1980  auto *CE = E.dyn_cast<const CXXMemberCallExpr *>();
1981  auto *D = E.dyn_cast<const CXXDeleteExpr *>();
1982  assert((CE != nullptr) ^ (D != nullptr));
1983  assert(CE == nullptr || CE->arg_begin() == CE->arg_end());
1984  assert(DtorType == Dtor_Deleting || DtorType == Dtor_Complete);
1985 
1986  // We have only one destructor in the vftable but can get both behaviors
1987  // by passing an implicit int parameter.
1988  GlobalDecl GD(Dtor, Dtor_Deleting);
1989  const CGFunctionInfo *FInfo =
1990  &CGM.getTypes().arrangeCXXStructorDeclaration(GD);
1991  llvm::FunctionType *Ty = CGF.CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(*FInfo);
1992  CGCallee Callee = CGCallee::forVirtual(CE, GD, This, Ty);
1993 
1994  ASTContext &Context = getContext();
1995  llvm::Value *ImplicitParam = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
1996  llvm::IntegerType::getInt32Ty(CGF.getLLVMContext()),
1997  DtorType == Dtor_Deleting);
1998 
1999  QualType ThisTy;
2000  if (CE) {
2001  ThisTy = CE->getObjectType();
2002  } else {
2003  ThisTy = D->getDestroyedType();
2004  }
2005 
2006  This = adjustThisArgumentForVirtualFunctionCall(CGF, GD, This, true);
2007  RValue RV =
2008  CGF.EmitCXXDestructorCall(GD, Callee, This.emitRawPointer(CGF), ThisTy,
2009  ImplicitParam, Context.IntTy, CE);
2010  return RV.getScalarVal();
2011 }

2013 const VBTableGlobals &
2014 MicrosoftCXXABI::enumerateVBTables(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2015  // At this layer, we can key the cache off of a single class, which is much
2016  // easier than caching each vbtable individually.
2017  llvm::DenseMap<const CXXRecordDecl*, VBTableGlobals>::iterator Entry;
2018  bool Added;
2019  std::tie(Entry, Added) =
2020  VBTablesMap.insert(std::make_pair(RD, VBTableGlobals()));
2021  VBTableGlobals &VBGlobals = Entry->second;
2022  if (!Added)
2023  return VBGlobals;
2024 
2025  MicrosoftVTableContext &Context = CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext();
2026  VBGlobals.VBTables = &Context.enumerateVBTables(RD);
2027 
2028  // Cache the globals for all vbtables so we don't have to recompute the
2029  // mangled names.
2030  llvm::GlobalVariable::LinkageTypes Linkage = CGM.getVTableLinkage(RD);
2031  for (VPtrInfoVector::const_iterator I = VBGlobals.VBTables->begin(),
2032  E = VBGlobals.VBTables->end();
2033  I != E; ++I) {
2034  VBGlobals.Globals.push_back(getAddrOfVBTable(**I, RD, Linkage));
2035  }
2036 
2037  return VBGlobals;
2038 }

2040 llvm::Function *
2041 MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitVirtualMemPtrThunk(const CXXMethodDecl *MD,
2042  const MethodVFTableLocation &ML) {
2043  assert(!isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(MD) && !isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD) &&
2044  "can't form pointers to ctors or virtual dtors");
2045 
2046  // Calculate the mangled name.
2047  SmallString<256> ThunkName;
2048  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(ThunkName);
2049  getMangleContext().mangleVirtualMemPtrThunk(MD, ML, Out);
2050 
2051  // If the thunk has been generated previously, just return it.
2052  if (llvm::GlobalValue *GV = CGM.getModule().getNamedValue(ThunkName))
2053  return cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
2054 
2055  // Create the llvm::Function.
2056  const CGFunctionInfo &FnInfo =
2057  CGM.getTypes().arrangeUnprototypedMustTailThunk(MD);
2058  llvm::FunctionType *ThunkTy = CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(FnInfo);
2059  llvm::Function *ThunkFn =
2060  llvm::Function::Create(ThunkTy, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
2061  ThunkName.str(), &CGM.getModule());
2062  assert(ThunkFn->getName() == ThunkName && "name was uniqued!");
2063 
2064  ThunkFn->setLinkage(MD->isExternallyVisible()
2065  ? llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage
2066  : llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage);
2067  if (MD->isExternallyVisible())
2068  ThunkFn->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(ThunkFn->getName()));
2069 
2070  CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(MD, FnInfo, ThunkFn, /*IsThunk=*/false);
2071  CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributesForDefinition(MD, ThunkFn);
2072 
2073  // Add the "thunk" attribute so that LLVM knows that the return type is
2074  // meaningless. These thunks can be used to call functions with differing
2075  // return types, and the caller is required to cast the prototype
2076  // appropriately to extract the correct value.
2077  ThunkFn->addFnAttr("thunk");
2078 
2079  // These thunks can be compared, so they are not unnamed.
2080  ThunkFn->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::None);
2081 
2082  // Start codegen.
2083  CodeGenFunction CGF(CGM);
2084  CGF.CurGD = GlobalDecl(MD);
2085  CGF.CurFuncIsThunk = true;
2086 
2087  // Build FunctionArgs, but only include the implicit 'this' parameter
2088  // declaration.
2089  FunctionArgList FunctionArgs;
2090  buildThisParam(CGF, FunctionArgs);
2091 
2092  // Start defining the function.
2093  CGF.StartFunction(GlobalDecl(), FnInfo.getReturnType(), ThunkFn, FnInfo,
2094  FunctionArgs, MD->getLocation(), SourceLocation());
2095 
2096  ApplyDebugLocation AL(CGF, MD->getLocation());
2097  setCXXABIThisValue(CGF, loadIncomingCXXThis(CGF));
2098 
2099  // Load the vfptr and then callee from the vftable. The callee should have
2100  // adjusted 'this' so that the vfptr is at offset zero.
2101  llvm::Type *ThunkPtrTy = ThunkTy->getPointerTo();
2102  llvm::Value *VTable = CGF.GetVTablePtr(
2103  getThisAddress(CGF), ThunkPtrTy->getPointerTo(), MD->getParent());
2104 
2105  llvm::Value *VFuncPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(
2106  ThunkPtrTy, VTable, ML.Index, "vfn");
2107  llvm::Value *Callee =
2108  CGF.Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(ThunkPtrTy, VFuncPtr, CGF.getPointerAlign());
2109 
2110  CGF.EmitMustTailThunk(MD, getThisValue(CGF), {ThunkTy, Callee});
2111 
2112  return ThunkFn;
2113 }

2155 void MicrosoftCXXABI::emitVBTableDefinition(const VPtrInfo &VBT,
2156  const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
2157  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV) const {
2158  const CXXRecordDecl *ObjectWithVPtr = VBT.ObjectWithVPtr;
2159 
2160  assert(RD->getNumVBases() && ObjectWithVPtr->getNumVBases() &&
2161  "should only emit vbtables for classes with vbtables");
2162 
2163  const ASTRecordLayout &BaseLayout =
2164  getContext().getASTRecordLayout(VBT.IntroducingObject);
2165  const ASTRecordLayout &DerivedLayout = getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2166 
2167  SmallVector<llvm::Constant *, 4> Offsets(1 + ObjectWithVPtr->getNumVBases(),
2168  nullptr);
2169 
2170  // The offset from ObjectWithVPtr's vbptr to itself always leads.
2171  CharUnits VBPtrOffset = BaseLayout.getVBPtrOffset();
2172  Offsets[0] = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, -VBPtrOffset.getQuantity());
2173 
2174  MicrosoftVTableContext &Context = CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext();
2175  for (const auto &I : ObjectWithVPtr->vbases()) {
2176  const CXXRecordDecl *VBase = I.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2177  CharUnits Offset = DerivedLayout.getVBaseClassOffset(VBase);
2178  assert(!Offset.isNegative());
2179 
2180  // Make it relative to the subobject vbptr.
2181  CharUnits CompleteVBPtrOffset = VBT.NonVirtualOffset + VBPtrOffset;
2182  if (VBT.getVBaseWithVPtr())
2183  CompleteVBPtrOffset +=
2184  DerivedLayout.getVBaseClassOffset(VBT.getVBaseWithVPtr());
2185  Offset -= CompleteVBPtrOffset;
2186 
2187  unsigned VBIndex = Context.getVBTableIndex(ObjectWithVPtr, VBase);
2188  assert(Offsets[VBIndex] == nullptr && "The same vbindex seen twice?");
2189  Offsets[VBIndex] = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, Offset.getQuantity());
2190  }
2191 
2192  assert(Offsets.size() ==
2193  cast<llvm::ArrayType>(GV->getValueType())->getNumElements());
2194  llvm::ArrayType *VBTableType =
2195  llvm::ArrayType::get(CGM.IntTy, Offsets.size());
2196  llvm::Constant *Init = llvm::ConstantArray::get(VBTableType, Offsets);
2197  GV->setInitializer(Init);
2198 
2199  if (RD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
2200  GV->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalVariable::AvailableExternallyLinkage);
2201 }

2203 llvm::Value *MicrosoftCXXABI::performThisAdjustment(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2204  Address This,
2205  const ThisAdjustment &TA) {
2206  if (TA.isEmpty())
2207  return This.emitRawPointer(CGF);
2208 
2209  This = This.withElementType(CGF.Int8Ty);
2210 
2211  llvm::Value *V;
2212  if (TA.Virtual.isEmpty()) {
2213  V = This.emitRawPointer(CGF);
2214  } else {
2215  assert(TA.Virtual.Microsoft.VtordispOffset < 0);
2216  // Adjust the this argument based on the vtordisp value.
2217  Address VtorDispPtr =
2218  CGF.Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(This,
2219  CharUnits::fromQuantity(TA.Virtual.Microsoft.VtordispOffset));
2220  VtorDispPtr = VtorDispPtr.withElementType(CGF.Int32Ty);
2221  llvm::Value *VtorDisp = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(VtorDispPtr, "vtordisp");
2222  V = CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(This.getElementType(), This.emitRawPointer(CGF),
2223  CGF.Builder.CreateNeg(VtorDisp));
2224 
2225  // Unfortunately, having applied the vtordisp means that we no
2226  // longer really have a known alignment for the vbptr step.
2227  // We'll assume the vbptr is pointer-aligned.
2228 
2229  if (TA.Virtual.Microsoft.VBPtrOffset) {
2230  // If the final overrider is defined in a virtual base other than the one
2231  // that holds the vfptr, we have to use a vtordispex thunk which looks up
2232  // the vbtable of the derived class.
2233  assert(TA.Virtual.Microsoft.VBPtrOffset > 0);
2234  assert(TA.Virtual.Microsoft.VBOffsetOffset >= 0);
2235  llvm::Value *VBPtr;
2236  llvm::Value *VBaseOffset = GetVBaseOffsetFromVBPtr(
2237  CGF, Address(V, CGF.Int8Ty, CGF.getPointerAlign()),
2238  -TA.Virtual.Microsoft.VBPtrOffset,
2239  TA.Virtual.Microsoft.VBOffsetOffset, &VBPtr);
2240  V = CGF.Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, VBPtr, VBaseOffset);
2241  }
2242  }
2243 
2244  if (TA.NonVirtual) {
2245  // Non-virtual adjustment might result in a pointer outside the allocated
2246  // object, e.g. if the final overrider class is laid out after the virtual
2247  // base that declares a method in the most derived class.
2248  V = CGF.Builder.CreateConstGEP1_32(CGF.Int8Ty, V, TA.NonVirtual);
2249  }
2250 
2251  // Don't need to bitcast back, the call CodeGen will handle this.
2252  return V;
2253 }

2255 llvm::Value *
2256 MicrosoftCXXABI::performReturnAdjustment(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address Ret,
2257  const ReturnAdjustment &RA) {
2258  if (RA.isEmpty())
2259  return Ret.emitRawPointer(CGF);
2260 
2261  Ret = Ret.withElementType(CGF.Int8Ty);
2262 
2263  llvm::Value *V = Ret.emitRawPointer(CGF);
2264  if (RA.Virtual.Microsoft.VBIndex) {
2265  assert(RA.Virtual.Microsoft.VBIndex > 0);

2366 void MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitThreadLocalInitFuncs(
2367  CodeGenModule &CGM, ArrayRef<const VarDecl *> CXXThreadLocals,
2368  ArrayRef<llvm::Function *> CXXThreadLocalInits,
2369  ArrayRef<const VarDecl *> CXXThreadLocalInitVars) {
2370  if (CXXThreadLocalInits.empty())

2373  CGM.AppendLinkerOptions(CGM.getTarget().getTriple().getArch() ==
2374  llvm::Triple::x86
2375  ? "/include:___dyn_tls_init@12"
2376  : "/include:__dyn_tls_init");

2378  // This will create a GV in the .CRT$XDU section. It will point to our
2379  // initialization function. The CRT will call all of these function
2380  // pointers at start-up time and, eventually, at thread-creation time.
2381  auto AddToXDU = [&CGM](llvm::Function *InitFunc) {
2382  llvm::GlobalVariable *InitFuncPtr = new llvm::GlobalVariable(

2388  // ensure it won't get discarded.

2392

2394  for (size_t I = 0, E = CXXThreadLocalInitVars.size(); I != E; ++I) {

2397  llvm::Function *F = CXXThreadLocalInits[I];

2399  // If the GV is already in a comdat group, then we have to join it.
2400  if (llvm::Comdat *C = GV->getComdat())
2401  AddToXDU(F)->setComdat(C);
2402  else

2404  }
2405

2408  llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, /*isVarArg=*/false);

2410  FTy, "__tls_init", CGM.getTypes().arrangeNullaryFunction(),
2411  SourceLocation(), /*TLS=*/true);
2412  CodeGenFunction(CGM).GenerateCXXGlobalInitFunc(InitFunc, NonComdatInits);
2413

2447 static void emitTlsGuardCheck(CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::GlobalValue *TlsGuard,

2469 static void emitDynamicTlsInitialization(CodeGenFunction &CGF) {

2471  CGF.createBasicBlock("dyntls.dyn_init", CGF.CurFn);

2473  CGF.createBasicBlock("dyntls.continue", CGF.CurFn);

2558 namespace {
2559 struct ResetGuardBit final : EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
2560  Address Guard;
2561  unsigned GuardNum;
2562  ResetGuardBit(Address Guard, unsigned GuardNum)
2563  : Guard(Guard), GuardNum(GuardNum) {}
2564 
2565  void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags flags) override {
2566  // Reset the bit in the mask so that the static variable may be
2567  // reinitialized.

2570  llvm::ConstantInt *Mask =
2571  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.IntTy, ~(1ULL << GuardNum));
2572  Builder.CreateStore(Builder.CreateAnd(LI, Mask), Guard);
2573  }
2574 };

2587 void MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitGuardedInit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const VarDecl &D,
2588  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV,
2589  bool PerformInit) {
2590  // MSVC only uses guards for static locals.
2591  if (!D.isStaticLocal()) {
2592  assert(GV->hasWeakLinkage() || GV->hasLinkOnceLinkage());
2593  // GlobalOpt is allowed to discard the initializer, so use linkonce_odr.
2594  llvm::Function *F = CGF.CurFn;
2595  F->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage);
2596  F->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(F->getName()));
2597  CGF.EmitCXXGlobalVarDeclInit(D, GV, PerformInit);
2598  return;
2599  }
2600 
2601  bool ThreadlocalStatic = D.getTLSKind();
2602  bool ThreadsafeStatic = getContext().getLangOpts().ThreadsafeStatics;
2603 
2604  // Thread-safe static variables which aren't thread-specific have a
2605  // per-variable guard.
2606  bool HasPerVariableGuard = ThreadsafeStatic && !ThreadlocalStatic;
2607 
2608  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
2609  llvm::IntegerType *GuardTy = CGF.Int32Ty;
2610  llvm::ConstantInt *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::get(GuardTy, 0);
2611  CharUnits GuardAlign = CharUnits::fromQuantity(4);
2612 
2613  // Get the guard variable for this function if we have one already.
2614  GuardInfo *GI = nullptr;
2615  if (ThreadlocalStatic)
2616  GI = &ThreadLocalGuardVariableMap[D.getDeclContext()];
2617  else if (!ThreadsafeStatic)
2618  GI = &GuardVariableMap[D.getDeclContext()];
2619 
2620  llvm::GlobalVariable *GuardVar = GI ? GI->Guard : nullptr;
2621  unsigned GuardNum;
2622  if (D.isExternallyVisible()) {
2623  // Externally visible variables have to be numbered in Sema to properly
2624  // handle unreachable VarDecls.
2625  GuardNum = getContext().getStaticLocalNumber(&D);
2626  assert(GuardNum > 0);
2627  GuardNum--;
2628  } else if (HasPerVariableGuard) {
2629  GuardNum = ThreadSafeGuardNumMap[D.getDeclContext()]++;
2630  } else {
2631  // Non-externally visible variables are numbered here in CodeGen.
2632  GuardNum = GI->BitIndex++;
2633  }
2634 
2635  if (!HasPerVariableGuard && GuardNum >= 32) {
2636  if (D.isExternallyVisible())
2637  ErrorUnsupportedABI(CGF, "more than 32 guarded initializations");
2638  GuardNum %= 32;
2639  GuardVar = nullptr;
2640  }
2641 
2642  if (!GuardVar) {
2643  // Mangle the name for the guard.
2644  SmallString<256> GuardName;
2645  {
2646  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(GuardName);
2647  if (HasPerVariableGuard)
2648  getMangleContext().mangleThreadSafeStaticGuardVariable(&D, GuardNum,
2649  Out);
2650  else
2651  getMangleContext().mangleStaticGuardVariable(&D, Out);
2652  }
2653 
2654  // Create the guard variable with a zero-initializer. Just absorb linkage,
2655  // visibility and dll storage class from the guarded variable.
2656  GuardVar =
2657  new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), GuardTy, /*isConstant=*/false,
2658  GV->getLinkage(), Zero, GuardName.str());
2659  GuardVar->setVisibility(GV->getVisibility());
2660  GuardVar->setDLLStorageClass(GV->getDLLStorageClass());
2661  GuardVar->setAlignment(GuardAlign.getAsAlign());
2662  if (GuardVar->isWeakForLinker())
2663  GuardVar->setComdat(
2664  CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(GuardVar->getName()));
2665  if (D.getTLSKind())
2666  CGM.setTLSMode(GuardVar, D);
2667  if (GI && !HasPerVariableGuard)
2668  GI->Guard = GuardVar;
2669  }
2670 
2671  ConstantAddress GuardAddr(GuardVar, GuardTy, GuardAlign);
2672 
2673  assert(GuardVar->getLinkage() == GV->getLinkage() &&
2674  "static local from the same function had different linkage");
2675 
2676  if (!HasPerVariableGuard) {
2677  // Pseudo code for the test:
2678  // if (!(GuardVar & MyGuardBit)) {
2679  // GuardVar |= MyGuardBit;
2680  // ... initialize the object ...;
2681  // }
2682 
2683  // Test our bit from the guard variable.
2684  llvm::ConstantInt *Bit = llvm::ConstantInt::get(GuardTy, 1ULL << GuardNum);
2685  llvm::LoadInst *LI = Builder.CreateLoad(GuardAddr);
2686  llvm::Value *NeedsInit =
2687  Builder.CreateICmpEQ(Builder.CreateAnd(LI, Bit), Zero);
2688  llvm::BasicBlock *InitBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("init");
2689  llvm::BasicBlock *EndBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("init.end");
2690  CGF.EmitCXXGuardedInitBranch(NeedsInit, InitBlock, EndBlock,
2691  CodeGenFunction::GuardKind::VariableGuard, &D);
2692 
2693  // Set our bit in the guard variable and emit the initializer and add a global
2694  // destructor if appropriate.
2695  CGF.EmitBlock(InitBlock);
2696  Builder.CreateStore(Builder.CreateOr(LI, Bit), GuardAddr);
2697  CGF.EHStack.pushCleanup<ResetGuardBit>(EHCleanup, GuardAddr, GuardNum);
2698  CGF.EmitCXXGlobalVarDeclInit(D, GV, PerformInit);
2699  CGF.PopCleanupBlock();
2700  Builder.CreateBr(EndBlock);
2701 
2702  // Continue.
2703  CGF.EmitBlock(EndBlock);
2704  } else {
2705  // Pseudo code for the test:
2706  // if (TSS > _Init_thread_epoch) {
2707  // _Init_thread_header(&TSS);
2708  // if (TSS == -1) {
2709  // ... initialize the object ...;
2710  // _Init_thread_footer(&TSS);
2711  // }
2712  // }
2713  //
2714  // The algorithm is almost identical to what can be found in the appendix
2715  // found in N2325.
2716 
2717  // This BasicBLock determines whether or not we have any work to do.
2718  llvm::LoadInst *FirstGuardLoad = Builder.CreateLoad(GuardAddr);
2719  FirstGuardLoad->setOrdering(llvm::AtomicOrdering::Unordered);
2720  llvm::LoadInst *InitThreadEpoch =
2721  Builder.CreateLoad(getInitThreadEpochPtr(CGM));
2722  llvm::Value *IsUninitialized =
2723  Builder.CreateICmpSGT(FirstGuardLoad, InitThreadEpoch);
2724  llvm::BasicBlock *AttemptInitBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("init.attempt");
2725  llvm::BasicBlock *EndBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("init.end");
2726  CGF.EmitCXXGuardedInitBranch(IsUninitialized, AttemptInitBlock, EndBlock,
2727  CodeGenFunction::GuardKind::VariableGuard, &D);
2728 
2729  // This BasicBlock attempts to determine whether or not this thread is
2730  // responsible for doing the initialization.
2731  CGF.EmitBlock(AttemptInitBlock);
2732  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getInitThreadHeaderFn(CGM),
2733  GuardAddr.getPointer());
2734  llvm::LoadInst *SecondGuardLoad = Builder.CreateLoad(GuardAddr);
2735  SecondGuardLoad->setOrdering(llvm::AtomicOrdering::Unordered);
2736  llvm::Value *ShouldDoInit =
2737  Builder.CreateICmpEQ(SecondGuardLoad, getAllOnesInt());
2738  llvm::BasicBlock *InitBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("init");
2739  Builder.CreateCondBr(ShouldDoInit, InitBlock, EndBlock);
2740 
2741  // Ok, we ended up getting selected as the initializing thread.
2742  CGF.EmitBlock(InitBlock);
2743  CGF.EHStack.pushCleanup<CallInitThreadAbort>(EHCleanup, GuardAddr);
2744  CGF.EmitCXXGlobalVarDeclInit(D, GV, PerformInit);
2745  CGF.PopCleanupBlock();
2746  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(getInitThreadFooterFn(CGM),
2747  GuardAddr.getPointer());
2748  Builder.CreateBr(EndBlock);
2749 
2750  CGF.EmitBlock(EndBlock);
2751  }
2752 }

2754 bool MicrosoftCXXABI::isZeroInitializable(const MemberPointerType *MPT) {
2755  // Null-ness for function memptrs only depends on the first field, which is
2756  // the function pointer. The rest don't matter, so we can zero initialize.
2757  if (MPT->isMemberFunctionPointer())
2758  return true;
2759 
2760  // The virtual base adjustment field is always -1 for null, so if we have one
2761  // we can't zero initialize. The field offset is sometimes also -1 if 0 is a
2762  // valid field offset.
2763  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = MPT->getMostRecentCXXRecordDecl();
2764  MSInheritanceModel Inheritance = RD->getMSInheritanceModel();
2765  return (!inheritanceModelHasVBTableOffsetField(Inheritance) &&
2766  RD->nullFieldOffsetIsZero());
2767 }

2769 llvm::Type *
2770 MicrosoftCXXABI::ConvertMemberPointerType(const MemberPointerType *MPT) {
2771  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = MPT->getMostRecentCXXRecordDecl();
2772  MSInheritanceModel Inheritance = RD->getMSInheritanceModel();
2773  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 4> fields;
2774  if (MPT->isMemberFunctionPointer())
2775  fields.push_back(CGM.VoidPtrTy); // FunctionPointerOrVirtualThunk
2776  else
2777  fields.push_back(CGM.IntTy); // FieldOffset
2778 
2779  if (inheritanceModelHasNVOffsetField(MPT->isMemberFunctionPointer(),
2780  Inheritance))
2781  fields.push_back(CGM.IntTy);
2782  if (inheritanceModelHasVBPtrOffsetField(Inheritance))
2783  fields.push_back(CGM.IntTy);
2784  if (inheritanceModelHasVBTableOffsetField(Inheritance))
2785  fields.push_back(CGM.IntTy); // VirtualBaseAdjustmentOffset
2786 
2787  if (fields.size() == 1)
2788  return fields[0];
2789  return llvm::StructType::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), fields);
2790 }

2792 void MicrosoftCXXABI::
2793 GetNullMemberPointerFields(const MemberPointerType *MPT,
2794  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Constant *> &fields) {

2800  fields.push_back(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.VoidPtrTy));

2803  fields.push_back(getZeroInt()); // FieldOffset

2806  }
2807 
2808  if (inheritanceModelHasNVOffsetField(MPT->isMemberFunctionPointer(),
2809  Inheritance))

2811  if (inheritanceModelHasVBPtrOffsetField(Inheritance))
2812  fields.push_back(getZeroInt());
2813  if (inheritanceModelHasVBTableOffsetField(Inheritance))
2814  fields.push_back(getAllOnesInt());

2829 MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitFullMemberPointer(llvm::Constant *FirstField,
2830  bool IsMemberFunction,

2832  CharUnits NonVirtualBaseAdjustment,
2833  unsigned VBTableIndex) {

2835 
2836  // Single inheritance class member pointer are represented as scalars instead
2837  // of aggregates.
2838  if (inheritanceModelHasOnlyOneField(IsMemberFunction, Inheritance))

2856  if (inheritanceModelHasVBTableOffsetField(Inheritance))

2879 llvm::Constant *MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitMemberPointer(const APValue &MP,
2880  QualType MPType) {
2881  const MemberPointerType *DstTy = MPType->castAs<MemberPointerType>();
2882  const ValueDecl *MPD = MP.getMemberPointerDecl();
2883  if (!MPD)
2884  return EmitNullMemberPointer(DstTy);
2885 
2886  ASTContext &Ctx = getContext();
2887  ArrayRef<const CXXRecordDecl *> MemberPointerPath = MP.getMemberPointerPath();
2888 
2889  llvm::Constant *C;
2890  if (const CXXMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(MPD)) {
2891  C = EmitMemberFunctionPointer(MD);
2892  } else {
2893  // For a pointer to data member, start off with the offset of the field in
2894  // the class in which it was declared, and convert from there if necessary.
2895  // For indirect field decls, get the outermost anonymous field and use the
2896  // parent class.
2897  CharUnits FieldOffset = Ctx.toCharUnitsFromBits(Ctx.getFieldOffset(MPD));
2898  const FieldDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(MPD);
2899  if (!FD)
2900  FD = cast<FieldDecl>(*cast<IndirectFieldDecl>(MPD)->chain_begin());
2901  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(FD->getParent());
2902  RD = RD->getMostRecentNonInjectedDecl();
2903  C = EmitMemberDataPointer(RD, FieldOffset);
2904  }
2905 
2906  if (!MemberPointerPath.empty()) {
2907  const CXXRecordDecl *SrcRD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(MPD->getDeclContext());
2908  const Type *SrcRecTy = Ctx.getTypeDeclType(SrcRD).getTypePtr();
2909  const MemberPointerType *SrcTy =
2910  Ctx.getMemberPointerType(DstTy->getPointeeType(), SrcRecTy)
2911  ->castAs<MemberPointerType>();
2912 
2913  bool DerivedMember = MP.isMemberPointerToDerivedMember();
2914  SmallVector<const CXXBaseSpecifier *, 4> DerivedToBasePath;
2915  const CXXRecordDecl *PrevRD = SrcRD;
2916  for (const CXXRecordDecl *PathElem : MemberPointerPath) {
2917  const CXXRecordDecl *Base = nullptr;
2918  const CXXRecordDecl *Derived = nullptr;
2919  if (DerivedMember) {
2920  Base = PathElem;
2921  Derived = PrevRD;
2922  } else {
2923  Base = PrevRD;
2924  Derived = PathElem;
2925  }
2926  for (const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS : Derived->bases())
2927  if (BS.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl()->getCanonicalDecl() ==
2928  Base->getCanonicalDecl())
2929  DerivedToBasePath.push_back(&BS);
2930  PrevRD = PathElem;
2931  }
2932  assert(DerivedToBasePath.size() == MemberPointerPath.size());
2933 
2934  CastKind CK = DerivedMember ? CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer
2935  : CK_BaseToDerivedMemberPointer;
2936  C = EmitMemberPointerConversion(SrcTy, DstTy, CK, DerivedToBasePath.begin(),
2937  DerivedToBasePath.end(), C);
2938  }
2939  return C;
2940 }

2942 llvm::Constant *
2943 MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitMemberFunctionPointer(const CXXMethodDecl *MD) {
2944  assert(MD->isInstance() && "Member function must not be static!");
2945 
2946  CharUnits NonVirtualBaseAdjustment = CharUnits::Zero();
2947  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = MD->getParent()->getMostRecentNonInjectedDecl();
2948  CodeGenTypes &Types = CGM.getTypes();
2949 
2950  unsigned VBTableIndex = 0;
2951  llvm::Constant *FirstField;
2952  const FunctionProtoType *FPT = MD->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
2953  if (!MD->isVirtual()) {
2954  llvm::Type *Ty;
2955  // Check whether the function has a computable LLVM signature.
2956  if (Types.isFuncTypeConvertible(FPT)) {
2957  // The function has a computable LLVM signature; use the correct type.
2958  Ty = Types.GetFunctionType(Types.arrangeCXXMethodDeclaration(MD));
2959  } else {
2960  // Use an arbitrary non-function type to tell GetAddrOfFunction that the
2961  // function type is incomplete.
2962  Ty = CGM.PtrDiffTy;
2963  }
2964  FirstField = CGM.GetAddrOfFunction(MD, Ty);
2965  } else {
2966  auto &VTableContext = CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext();
2967  MethodVFTableLocation ML = VTableContext.getMethodVFTableLocation(MD);
2968  FirstField = EmitVirtualMemPtrThunk(MD, ML);
2969  // Include the vfptr adjustment if the method is in a non-primary vftable.
2970  NonVirtualBaseAdjustment += ML.VFPtrOffset;
2971  if (ML.VBase)
2972  VBTableIndex = VTableContext.getVBTableIndex(RD, ML.VBase) * 4;
2973  }
2974 
2975  if (VBTableIndex == 0 &&
2976  RD->getMSInheritanceModel() ==
2977  MSInheritanceModel::Virtual)
2978  NonVirtualBaseAdjustment -= getContext().getOffsetOfBaseWithVBPtr(RD);
2979 
2980  // The rest of the fields are common with data member pointers.
2981  return EmitFullMemberPointer(FirstField, /*IsMemberFunction=*/true, RD,
2982  NonVirtualBaseAdjustment, VBTableIndex);
2983 }

2985 /// Member pointers are the same if they're either bitwise identical *or* both
2986 /// null. Null-ness for function members is determined by the first field,
2987 /// while for data member pointers we must compare all fields.
2988 llvm::Value *
2989 MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitMemberPointerComparison(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2990  llvm::Value *L,
2991  llvm::Value *R,
2992  const MemberPointerType *MPT,
2993  bool Inequality) {
2994  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
2995 
2996  // Handle != comparisons by switching the sense of all boolean operations.
2997  llvm::ICmpInst::Predicate Eq;
2998  llvm::Instruction::BinaryOps And, Or;
2999  if (Inequality) {
3000  Eq = llvm::ICmpInst::ICMP_NE;
3001  And = llvm::Instruction::Or;
3002  Or = llvm::Instruction::And;
3003  } else {
3004  Eq = llvm::ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ;
3005  And = llvm::Instruction::And;
3006  Or = llvm::Instruction::Or;
3007  }
3008 
3009  // If this is a single field member pointer (single inheritance), this is a
3010  // single icmp.
3011  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = MPT->getMostRecentCXXRecordDecl();
3012  MSInheritanceModel Inheritance = RD->getMSInheritanceModel();
3013  if (inheritanceModelHasOnlyOneField(MPT->isMemberFunctionPointer(),
3014  Inheritance))
3015  return Builder.CreateICmp(Eq, L, R);
3016 
3017  // Compare the first field.
3018  llvm::Value *L0 = Builder.CreateExtractValue(L, 0, "lhs.0");
3019  llvm::Value *R0 = Builder.CreateExtractValue(R, 0, "rhs.0");
3020  llvm::Value *Cmp0 = Builder.CreateICmp(Eq, L0, R0, "memptr.cmp.first");
3021 
3022  // Compare everything other than the first field.
3023  llvm::Value *Res = nullptr;
3024  llvm::StructType *LType = cast<llvm::StructType>(L->getType());
3025  for (unsigned I = 1, E = LType->getNumElements(); I != E; ++I) {
3026  llvm::Value *LF = Builder.CreateExtractValue(L, I);
3027  llvm::Value *RF = Builder.CreateExtractValue(R, I);
3028  llvm::Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmp(Eq, LF, RF, "memptr.cmp.rest");
3029  if (Res)
3030  Res = Builder.CreateBinOp(And, Res, Cmp);
3031  else
3032  Res = Cmp;
3033  }
3034 
3035  // Check if the first field is 0 if this is a function pointer.
3036  if (MPT->isMemberFunctionPointer()) {
3037  // (l1 == r1 && ...) || l0 == 0
3038  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(L0->getType());
3039  llvm::Value *IsZero = Builder.CreateICmp(Eq, L0, Zero, "memptr.cmp.iszero");
3040  Res = Builder.CreateBinOp(Or, Res, IsZero);
3041  }
3042 
3043  // Combine the comparison of the first field, which must always be true for
3044  // this comparison to succeeed.
3045  return Builder.CreateBinOp(And, Res, Cmp0, "memptr.cmp");
3046 }

3048 llvm::Value *
3049 MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitMemberPointerIsNotNull(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3050  llvm::Value *MemPtr,
3051  const MemberPointerType *MPT) {
3052  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
3053  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Constant *, 4> fields;
3054  // We only need one field for member functions.
3055  if (MPT->isMemberFunctionPointer())
3056  fields.push_back(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.VoidPtrTy));
3057  else
3058  GetNullMemberPointerFields(MPT, fields);
3059  assert(!fields.empty());
3060  llvm::Value *FirstField = MemPtr;
3061  if (MemPtr->getType()->isStructTy())
3062  FirstField = Builder.CreateExtractValue(MemPtr, 0);
3063  llvm::Value *Res = Builder.CreateICmpNE(FirstField, fields[0], "memptr.cmp0");
3064 
3065  // For function member pointers, we only need to test the function pointer
3066  // field. The other fields if any can be garbage.
3067  if (MPT->isMemberFunctionPointer())
3068  return Res;
3069 
3070  // Otherwise, emit a series of compares and combine the results.
3071  for (int I = 1, E = fields.size(); I < E; ++I) {
3072  llvm::Value *Field = Builder.CreateExtractValue(MemPtr, I);
3073  llvm::Value *Next = Builder.CreateICmpNE(Field, fields[I], "memptr.cmp");
3074  Res = Builder.CreateOr(Res, Next, "memptr.tobool");
3075  }
3076  return Res;
3077 }

3079 bool MicrosoftCXXABI::MemberPointerConstantIsNull(const MemberPointerType *MPT,
3080  llvm::Constant *Val) {
3081  // Function pointers are null if the pointer in the first field is null.
3082  if (MPT->isMemberFunctionPointer()) {
3083  llvm::Constant *FirstField = Val->getType()->isStructTy() ?
3084  Val->getAggregateElement(0U) : Val;
3085  return FirstField->isNullValue();
3086  }
3087 
3088  // If it's not a function pointer and it's zero initializable, we can easily
3089  // check zero.
3090  if (isZeroInitializable(MPT) && Val->isNullValue())
3091  return true;
3092 
3093  // Otherwise, break down all the fields for comparison. Hopefully these
3094  // little Constants are reused, while a big null struct might not be.
3095  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Constant *, 4> Fields;
3096  GetNullMemberPointerFields(MPT, Fields);
3097  if (Fields.size() == 1) {
3098  assert(Val->getType()->isIntegerTy());
3099  return Val == Fields[0];
3100  }
3101 
3102  unsigned I, E;
3103  for (I = 0, E = Fields.size(); I != E; ++I) {
3104  if (Val->getAggregateElement(I) != Fields[I])
3105  break;
3106  }
3107  return I == E;
3108 }
