3146 // Returns an adjusted base cast to i8*, since we do more address arithmetic on
3147 // it.
3148 llvm::Value *MicrosoftCXXABI::AdjustVirtualBase(
3149  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *E, const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
3150  Address Base, llvm::Value *VBTableOffset, llvm::Value *VBPtrOffset) {
3151  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
3152  Base = Base.withElementType(CGM.Int8Ty);
3153  llvm::BasicBlock *OriginalBB = nullptr;
3154  llvm::BasicBlock *SkipAdjustBB = nullptr;
3155  llvm::BasicBlock *VBaseAdjustBB = nullptr;
3156 
3157  // In the unspecified inheritance model, there might not be a vbtable at all,
3158  // in which case we need to skip the virtual base lookup. If there is a
3159  // vbtable, the first entry is a no-op entry that gives back the original
3160  // base, so look for a virtual base adjustment offset of zero.
3161  if (VBPtrOffset) {
3162  OriginalBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3163  VBaseAdjustBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("memptr.vadjust");
3164  SkipAdjustBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("memptr.skip_vadjust");
3165  llvm::Value *IsVirtual =
3166  Builder.CreateICmpNE(VBTableOffset, getZeroInt(),
3167  "memptr.is_vbase");
3168  Builder.CreateCondBr(IsVirtual, VBaseAdjustBB, SkipAdjustBB);
3169  CGF.EmitBlock(VBaseAdjustBB);
3170  }
3171 
3172  // If we weren't given a dynamic vbptr offset, RD should be complete and we'll
3173  // know the vbptr offset.
3174  if (!VBPtrOffset) {
3175  CharUnits offs = CharUnits::Zero();
3176  if (!RD->hasDefinition()) {
3177  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = CGF.CGM.getDiags();
3178  unsigned DiagID = Diags.getCustomDiagID(
3179  DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
3180  "member pointer representation requires a "
3181  "complete class type for %0 to perform this expression");
3182  Diags.Report(E->getExprLoc(), DiagID) << RD << E->getSourceRange();
3183  } else if (RD->getNumVBases())
3184  offs = getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD).getVBPtrOffset();
3185  VBPtrOffset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, offs.getQuantity());
3186  }
3187  llvm::Value *VBPtr = nullptr;
3188  llvm::Value *VBaseOffs =
3189  GetVBaseOffsetFromVBPtr(CGF, Base, VBPtrOffset, VBTableOffset, &VBPtr);
3190  llvm::Value *AdjustedBase =
3191  Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(CGM.Int8Ty, VBPtr, VBaseOffs);
3192 
3193  // Merge control flow with the case where we didn't have to adjust.
3194  if (VBaseAdjustBB) {
3195  Builder.CreateBr(SkipAdjustBB);
3196  CGF.EmitBlock(SkipAdjustBB);
3197  llvm::PHINode *Phi = Builder.CreatePHI(CGM.Int8PtrTy, 2, "memptr.base");
3198  Phi->addIncoming(Base.emitRawPointer(CGF), OriginalBB);
3199  Phi->addIncoming(AdjustedBase, VBaseAdjustBB);
3200  return Phi;
3201  }
3202  return AdjustedBase;
3203 }

3205 llvm::Value *MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitMemberDataPointerAddress(
3206  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *E, Address Base, llvm::Value *MemPtr,
3207  const MemberPointerType *MPT) {
3208  assert(MPT->isMemberDataPointer());
3209  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
3210  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = MPT->getMostRecentCXXRecordDecl();
3211  MSInheritanceModel Inheritance = RD->getMSInheritanceModel();
3212 
3213  // Extract the fields we need, regardless of model. We'll apply them if we
3214  // have them.
3215  llvm::Value *FieldOffset = MemPtr;
3216  llvm::Value *VirtualBaseAdjustmentOffset = nullptr;
3217  llvm::Value *VBPtrOffset = nullptr;
3218  if (MemPtr->getType()->isStructTy()) {
3219  // We need to extract values.
3220  unsigned I = 0;
3221  FieldOffset = Builder.CreateExtractValue(MemPtr, I++);
3222  if (inheritanceModelHasVBPtrOffsetField(Inheritance))
3223  VBPtrOffset = Builder.CreateExtractValue(MemPtr, I++);
3224  if (inheritanceModelHasVBTableOffsetField(Inheritance))
3225  VirtualBaseAdjustmentOffset = Builder.CreateExtractValue(MemPtr, I++);

3229  if (VirtualBaseAdjustmentOffset) {
3230  Addr = AdjustVirtualBase(CGF, E, RD, Base, VirtualBaseAdjustmentOffset,
3231  VBPtrOffset);
3232  } else {
3233  Addr = Base.emitRawPointer(CGF);
3234  }
3235 
3236  // Apply the offset, which we assume is non-null.
3237  return Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, Addr, FieldOffset,
3238  "memptr.offset");
3239 }
3240 
3241 llvm::Value *
3242 MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitMemberPointerConversion(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3243  const CastExpr *E,
3244  llvm::Value *Src) {
3245  assert(E->getCastKind() == CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer ||
3246  E->getCastKind() == CK_BaseToDerivedMemberPointer ||
3247  E->getCastKind() == CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer);
3248 
3249  // Use constant emission if we can.
3250  if (isa<llvm::Constant>(Src))
3251  return EmitMemberPointerConversion(E, cast<llvm::Constant>(Src));
3252 
3253  // We may be adding or dropping fields from the member pointer, so we need
3254  // both types and the inheritance models of both records.
3255  const MemberPointerType *SrcTy =
3256  E->getSubExpr()->getType()->castAs<MemberPointerType>();
3257  const MemberPointerType *DstTy = E->getType()->castAs<MemberPointerType>();
3258  bool IsFunc = SrcTy->isMemberFunctionPointer();
3259 
3260  // If the classes use the same null representation, reinterpret_cast is a nop.
3261  bool IsReinterpret = E->getCastKind() == CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer;
3262  if (IsReinterpret && IsFunc)
3263  return Src;
3264 
3265  CXXRecordDecl *SrcRD = SrcTy->getMostRecentCXXRecordDecl();
3266  CXXRecordDecl *DstRD = DstTy->getMostRecentCXXRecordDecl();
3267  if (IsReinterpret &&
3268  SrcRD->nullFieldOffsetIsZero() == DstRD->nullFieldOffsetIsZero())
3269  return Src;
3270 
3271  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
3272 
3273  // Branch past the conversion if Src is null.
3274  llvm::Value *IsNotNull = EmitMemberPointerIsNotNull(CGF, Src, SrcTy);
3275  llvm::Constant *DstNull = EmitNullMemberPointer(DstTy);
3276 
3277  // C++ 5.2.10p9: The null member pointer value is converted to the null member
3278  // pointer value of the destination type.
3279  if (IsReinterpret) {
3280  // For reinterpret casts, sema ensures that src and dst are both functions
3281  // or data and have the same size, which means the LLVM types should match.
3282  assert(Src->getType() == DstNull->getType());
3283  return Builder.CreateSelect(IsNotNull, Src, DstNull);
3284  }
3285 
3286  llvm::BasicBlock *OriginalBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3287  llvm::BasicBlock *ConvertBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("memptr.convert");
3288  llvm::BasicBlock *ContinueBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("memptr.converted");
3289  Builder.CreateCondBr(IsNotNull, ConvertBB, ContinueBB);
3290  CGF.EmitBlock(ConvertBB);
3291 
3292  llvm::Value *Dst = EmitNonNullMemberPointerConversion(
3293  SrcTy, DstTy, E->getCastKind(), E->path_begin(), E->path_end(), Src,
3294  Builder);
3295 
3296  Builder.CreateBr(ContinueBB);
3297 
3298  // In the continuation, choose between DstNull and Dst.
3299  CGF.EmitBlock(ContinueBB);
3300  llvm::PHINode *Phi = Builder.CreatePHI(DstNull->getType(), 2, "memptr.converted");
3301  Phi->addIncoming(DstNull, OriginalBB);
3302  Phi->addIncoming(Dst, ConvertBB);
3303  return Phi;
3304 }
3305 
3306 llvm::Value *MicrosoftCXXABI::EmitNonNullMemberPointerConversion(
3307  const MemberPointerType *SrcTy, const MemberPointerType *DstTy, CastKind CK,
3308  CastExpr::path_const_iterator PathBegin,
3309  CastExpr::path_const_iterator PathEnd, llvm::Value *Src,
3310  CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
3311  const CXXRecordDecl *SrcRD = SrcTy->getMostRecentCXXRecordDecl();
3312  const CXXRecordDecl *DstRD = DstTy->getMostRecentCXXRecordDecl();
3313  MSInheritanceModel SrcInheritance = SrcRD->getMSInheritanceModel();
3314  MSInheritanceModel DstInheritance = DstRD->getMSInheritanceModel();
3315  bool IsFunc = SrcTy->isMemberFunctionPointer();
3316  bool IsConstant = isa<llvm::Constant>(Src);
3317 
3318  // Decompose src.
3319  llvm::Value *FirstField = Src;
3320  llvm::Value *NonVirtualBaseAdjustment = getZeroInt();
3321  llvm::Value *VirtualBaseAdjustmentOffset = getZeroInt();
3322  llvm::Value *VBPtrOffset = getZeroInt();
3323  if (!inheritanceModelHasOnlyOneField(IsFunc, SrcInheritance)) {
3324  // We need to extract values.
3325  unsigned I = 0;
3326  FirstField = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Src, I++);
3327  if (inheritanceModelHasNVOffsetField(IsFunc, SrcInheritance))
3328  NonVirtualBaseAdjustment = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Src, I++);
3329  if (inheritanceModelHasVBPtrOffsetField(SrcInheritance))
3330  VBPtrOffset = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Src, I++);
3331  if (inheritanceModelHasVBTableOffsetField(SrcInheritance))
3332  VirtualBaseAdjustmentOffset = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Src, I++);
3333  }
3334 
3335  bool IsDerivedToBase = (CK == CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer);
3336  const MemberPointerType *DerivedTy = IsDerivedToBase ? SrcTy : DstTy;
3337  const CXXRecordDecl *DerivedClass = DerivedTy->getMostRecentCXXRecordDecl();
3338 
3339  // For data pointers, we adjust the field offset directly. For functions, we
3340  // have a separate field.
3341  llvm::Value *&NVAdjustField = IsFunc ? NonVirtualBaseAdjustment : FirstField;
3342 
3343  // The virtual inheritance model has a quirk: the virtual base table is always
3344  // referenced when dereferencing a member pointer even if the member pointer
3345  // is non-virtual. This is accounted for by adjusting the non-virtual offset
3346  // to point backwards to the top of the MDC from the first VBase. Undo this
3347  // adjustment to normalize the member pointer.
3348  llvm::Value *SrcVBIndexEqZero =
3349  Builder.CreateICmpEQ(VirtualBaseAdjustmentOffset, getZeroInt());
3350  if (SrcInheritance == MSInheritanceModel::Virtual) {
3351  if (int64_t SrcOffsetToFirstVBase =
3352  getContext().getOffsetOfBaseWithVBPtr(SrcRD).getQuantity()) {
3353  llvm::Value *UndoSrcAdjustment = Builder.CreateSelect(
3354  SrcVBIndexEqZero,
3355  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, SrcOffsetToFirstVBase),
3356  getZeroInt());
3357  NVAdjustField = Builder.CreateNSWAdd(NVAdjustField, UndoSrcAdjustment);
3358  }
3359  }
3360 
3361  // A non-zero vbindex implies that we are dealing with a source member in a
3362  // floating virtual base in addition to some non-virtual offset. If the
3363  // vbindex is zero, we are dealing with a source that exists in a non-virtual,
3364  // fixed, base. The difference between these two cases is that the vbindex +
3365  // nvoffset *always* point to the member regardless of what context they are
3366  // evaluated in so long as the vbindex is adjusted. A member inside a fixed
3367  // base requires explicit nv adjustment.
3368  llvm::Constant *BaseClassOffset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
3369  CGM.IntTy,
3370  CGM.computeNonVirtualBaseClassOffset(DerivedClass, PathBegin, PathEnd)
3371  .getQuantity());
3372 
3373  llvm::Value *NVDisp;
3374  if (IsDerivedToBase)
3375  NVDisp = Builder.CreateNSWSub(NVAdjustField, BaseClassOffset, "adj");
3376  else
3377  NVDisp = Builder.CreateNSWAdd(NVAdjustField, BaseClassOffset, "adj");
3378 
3379  NVAdjustField = Builder.CreateSelect(SrcVBIndexEqZero, NVDisp, getZeroInt());
3380 
3381  // Update the vbindex to an appropriate value in the destination because
3382  // SrcRD's vbtable might not be a strict prefix of the one in DstRD.
3383  llvm::Value *DstVBIndexEqZero = SrcVBIndexEqZero;
3384  if (inheritanceModelHasVBTableOffsetField(DstInheritance) &&
3385  inheritanceModelHasVBTableOffsetField(SrcInheritance)) {
3386  if (llvm::GlobalVariable *VDispMap =
3387  getAddrOfVirtualDisplacementMap(SrcRD, DstRD)) {
3388  llvm::Value *VBIndex = Builder.CreateExactUDiv(
3389  VirtualBaseAdjustmentOffset, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, 4));
3390  if (IsConstant) {
3391  llvm::Constant *Mapping = VDispMap->getInitializer();
3392  VirtualBaseAdjustmentOffset =
3393  Mapping->getAggregateElement(cast<llvm::Constant>(VBIndex));
3394  } else {
3395  llvm::Value *Idxs[] = {getZeroInt(), VBIndex};
3396  VirtualBaseAdjustmentOffset = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(
3397  CGM.IntTy, Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(VDispMap->getValueType(),
3398  VDispMap, Idxs),
3399  CharUnits::fromQuantity(4));
3400  }
3401 
3402  DstVBIndexEqZero =
3403  Builder.CreateICmpEQ(VirtualBaseAdjustmentOffset, getZeroInt());
3404  }
3405  }
3406 
3407  // Set the VBPtrOffset to zero if the vbindex is zero. Otherwise, initialize
3408  // it to the offset of the vbptr.
3409  if (inheritanceModelHasVBPtrOffsetField(DstInheritance)) {
3410  llvm::Value *DstVBPtrOffset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
3411  CGM.IntTy,
3412  getContext().getASTRecordLayout(DstRD).getVBPtrOffset().getQuantity());
3413  VBPtrOffset =
3414  Builder.CreateSelect(DstVBIndexEqZero, getZeroInt(), DstVBPtrOffset);
3415  }
3416 
3417  // Likewise, apply a similar adjustment so that dereferencing the member
3418  // pointer correctly accounts for the distance between the start of the first
3419  // virtual base and the top of the MDC.
3420  if (DstInheritance == MSInheritanceModel::Virtual) {
3421  if (int64_t DstOffsetToFirstVBase =
3422  getContext().getOffsetOfBaseWithVBPtr(DstRD).getQuantity()) {
3423  llvm::Value *DoDstAdjustment = Builder.CreateSelect(
3424  DstVBIndexEqZero,
3425  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, DstOffsetToFirstVBase),
3426  getZeroInt());
3427  NVAdjustField = Builder.CreateNSWSub(NVAdjustField, DoDstAdjustment);
3428  }
3429  }
3430 
3431  // Recompose dst from the null struct and the adjusted fields from src.
3432  llvm::Value *Dst;
3433  if (inheritanceModelHasOnlyOneField(IsFunc, DstInheritance)) {
3434  Dst = FirstField;
3435  } else {
3436  Dst = llvm::UndefValue::get(ConvertMemberPointerType(DstTy));
3437  unsigned Idx = 0;
3438  Dst = Builder.CreateInsertValue(Dst, FirstField, Idx++);
3439  if (inheritanceModelHasNVOffsetField(IsFunc, DstInheritance))
3440  Dst = Builder.CreateInsertValue(Dst, NonVirtualBaseAdjustment, Idx++);
3441  if (inheritanceModelHasVBPtrOffsetField(DstInheritance))
3442  Dst = Builder.CreateInsertValue(Dst, VBPtrOffset, Idx++);
3443  if (inheritanceModelHasVBTableOffsetField(DstInheritance))
3444  Dst = Builder.CreateInsertValue(Dst, VirtualBaseAdjustmentOffset, Idx++);
3445  }
3446  return Dst;
3447 }

3536 // MS RTTI Overview:
3537 // The run time type information emitted by cl.exe contains 5 distinct types of
3538 // structures. Many of them reference each other.
3539 //
3540 // TypeInfo: Static classes that are returned by typeid.
3541 //
3542 // CompleteObjectLocator: Referenced by vftables. They contain information
3543 // required for dynamic casting, including OffsetFromTop. They also contain
3544 // a reference to the TypeInfo for the type and a reference to the
3545 // CompleteHierarchyDescriptor for the type.
3546 //
3547 // ClassHierarchyDescriptor: Contains information about a class hierarchy.
3548 // Used during dynamic_cast to walk a class hierarchy. References a base
3549 // class array and the size of said array.
3550 //
3551 // BaseClassArray: Contains a list of classes in a hierarchy. BaseClassArray is
3552 // somewhat of a misnomer because the most derived class is also in the list
3553 // as well as multiple copies of virtual bases (if they occur multiple times
3554 // in the hierarchy.) The BaseClassArray contains one BaseClassDescriptor for
3555 // every path in the hierarchy, in pre-order depth first order. Note, we do
3556 // not declare a specific llvm type for BaseClassArray, it's merely an array
3557 // of BaseClassDescriptor pointers.
3558 //
3559 // BaseClassDescriptor: Contains information about a class in a class hierarchy.
3560 // BaseClassDescriptor is also somewhat of a misnomer for the same reason that
3561 // BaseClassArray is. It contains information about a class within a
3562 // hierarchy such as: is this base is ambiguous and what is its offset in the
3563 // vbtable. The names of the BaseClassDescriptors have all of their fields
3564 // mangled into them so they can be aggressively deduplicated by the linker.
3565 
3566 static llvm::GlobalVariable *getTypeInfoVTable(CodeGenModule &CGM) {
3567  StringRef MangledName("??_7type_info@@6B@");
3568  if (auto VTable = CGM.getModule().getNamedGlobal(MangledName))
3569  return VTable;
3570  return new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), CGM.Int8PtrTy,
3571  /*isConstant=*/true,
3572  llvm::GlobalVariable::ExternalLinkage,
3573  /*Initializer=*/nullptr, MangledName);
3574 }

3577 
3578 /// A Helper struct that stores information about a class in a class
3579 /// hierarchy. The information stored in these structs struct is used during
3580 /// the generation of ClassHierarchyDescriptors and BaseClassDescriptors.
3581 // During RTTI creation, MSRTTIClasses are stored in a contiguous array with
3582 // implicit depth first pre-order tree connectivity. getFirstChild and
3583 // getNextSibling allow us to walk the tree efficiently.
3584 struct MSRTTIClass {
3585  enum {
3586  IsPrivateOnPath = 1 | 8,
3587  IsAmbiguous = 2,
3588  IsPrivate = 4,
3589  IsVirtual = 16,
3590  HasHierarchyDescriptor = 64
3591  };
3592  MSRTTIClass(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) : RD(RD) {}
3593  uint32_t initialize(const MSRTTIClass *Parent,
3594  const CXXBaseSpecifier *Specifier);
3595 
3596  MSRTTIClass *getFirstChild() { return this + 1; }
3597  static MSRTTIClass *getNextChild(MSRTTIClass *Child) {
3598  return Child + 1 + Child->NumBases;
3599  }
3600 
3601  const CXXRecordDecl *RD, *VirtualRoot;
3602  uint32_t Flags, NumBases, OffsetInVBase;
3603 };
3604 
3605 /// Recursively initialize the base class array.
3606 uint32_t MSRTTIClass::initialize(const MSRTTIClass *Parent,
3607  const CXXBaseSpecifier *Specifier) {
3608  Flags = HasHierarchyDescriptor;
3609  if (!Parent) {
3610  VirtualRoot = nullptr;
3611  OffsetInVBase = 0;
3612  } else {
3613  if (Specifier->getAccessSpecifier() != AS_public)
3614  Flags |= IsPrivate | IsPrivateOnPath;
3615  if (Specifier->isVirtual()) {
3616  Flags |= IsVirtual;
3617  VirtualRoot = RD;
3618  OffsetInVBase = 0;
3619  } else {
3620  if (Parent->Flags & IsPrivateOnPath)
3621  Flags |= IsPrivateOnPath;
3622  VirtualRoot = Parent->VirtualRoot;
3623  OffsetInVBase = Parent->OffsetInVBase + RD->getASTContext()
3624  .getASTRecordLayout(Parent->RD).getBaseClassOffset(RD).getQuantity();
3625  }
3626  }
3627  NumBases = 0;
3628  MSRTTIClass *Child = getFirstChild();
3629  for (const CXXBaseSpecifier &Base : RD->bases()) {
3630  NumBases += Child->initialize(this, &Base) + 1;
3631  Child = getNextChild(Child);
3632  }
3633  return NumBases;
3634 }

3636 static llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes getLinkageForRTTI(QualType Ty) {
3637  switch (Ty->getLinkage()) {
3638  case Linkage::Invalid:
3639  llvm_unreachable("Linkage hasn't been computed!");
3640 
3641  case Linkage::None:
3642  case Linkage::Internal:
3643  case Linkage::UniqueExternal:
3644  return llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage;
3645 
3646  case Linkage::VisibleNone:
3647  case Linkage::Module:
3648  case Linkage::External:
3649  return llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage;
3650  }
3651  llvm_unreachable("Invalid linkage!");
3652 }

3687 /// Recursively serializes a class hierarchy in pre-order depth first
3688 /// order.
3689 static void serializeClassHierarchy(SmallVectorImpl<MSRTTIClass> &Classes,
3690  const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
3691  Classes.push_back(MSRTTIClass(RD));
3692  for (const CXXBaseSpecifier &Base : RD->bases())
3693  serializeClassHierarchy(Classes, Base.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
3694 }
3695 
3696 /// Find ambiguity among base classes.
3697 static void
3698 detectAmbiguousBases(SmallVectorImpl<MSRTTIClass> &Classes) {
3699  llvm::SmallPtrSet<const CXXRecordDecl *, 8> VirtualBases;
3700  llvm::SmallPtrSet<const CXXRecordDecl *, 8> UniqueBases;
3701  llvm::SmallPtrSet<const CXXRecordDecl *, 8> AmbiguousBases;
3702  for (MSRTTIClass *Class = &Classes.front(); Class <= &Classes.back();) {
3703  if ((Class->Flags & MSRTTIClass::IsVirtual) &&
3704  !VirtualBases.insert(Class->RD).second) {
3705  Class = MSRTTIClass::getNextChild(Class);
3706  continue;
3707  }
3708  if (!UniqueBases.insert(Class->RD).second)
3709  AmbiguousBases.insert(Class->RD);
3710  Class++;
3711  }
3712  if (AmbiguousBases.empty())
3713  return;
3714  for (MSRTTIClass &Class : Classes)
3715  if (AmbiguousBases.count(Class.RD))
3716  Class.Flags |= MSRTTIClass::IsAmbiguous;
3717 }
3718 
3719 llvm::GlobalVariable *MSRTTIBuilder::getClassHierarchyDescriptor() {
3720  SmallString<256> MangledName;
3721  {
3722  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(MangledName);
3723  ABI.getMangleContext().mangleCXXRTTIClassHierarchyDescriptor(RD, Out);
3724  }
3725 
3726  // Check to see if we've already declared this ClassHierarchyDescriptor.
3727  if (auto CHD = Module.getNamedGlobal(MangledName))
3728  return CHD;
3729 
3730  // Serialize the class hierarchy and initialize the CHD Fields.
3731  SmallVector<MSRTTIClass, 8> Classes;
3732  serializeClassHierarchy(Classes, RD);
3733  Classes.front().initialize(/*Parent=*/nullptr, /*Specifier=*/nullptr);
3734  detectAmbiguousBases(Classes);
3735  int Flags = 0;
3736  for (const MSRTTIClass &Class : Classes) {
3737  if (Class.RD->getNumBases() > 1)
3738  Flags |= HasBranchingHierarchy;
3739  // Note: cl.exe does not calculate "HasAmbiguousBases" correctly. We
3740  // believe the field isn't actually used.
3741  if (Class.Flags & MSRTTIClass::IsAmbiguous)
3742  Flags |= HasAmbiguousBases;
3743  }
3744  if ((Flags & HasBranchingHierarchy) && RD->getNumVBases() != 0)
3745  Flags |= HasVirtualBranchingHierarchy;
3746  // These gep indices are used to get the address of the first element of the
3747  // base class array.
3748  llvm::Value *GEPIndices[] = {llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, 0),
3749  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, 0)};
3750 
3751  // Forward-declare the class hierarchy descriptor
3752  auto Type = ABI.getClassHierarchyDescriptorType();
3753  auto CHD = new llvm::GlobalVariable(Module, Type, /*isConstant=*/true, Linkage,
3754  /*Initializer=*/nullptr,
3755  MangledName);
3756  if (CHD->isWeakForLinker())
3757  CHD->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(CHD->getName()));
3758 
3759  auto *Bases = getBaseClassArray(Classes);
3760 
3761  // Initialize the base class ClassHierarchyDescriptor.
3762  llvm::Constant *Fields[] = {
3763  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, 0), // reserved by the runtime
3764  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, Flags),
3765  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, Classes.size()),
3766  ABI.getImageRelativeConstant(llvm::ConstantExpr::getInBoundsGetElementPtr(
3767  Bases->getValueType(), Bases,
3768  llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Value *>(GEPIndices))),
3769  };
3770  CHD->setInitializer(llvm::ConstantStruct::get(Type, Fields));
3771  return CHD;
3772 }

3774 llvm::GlobalVariable *
3775 MSRTTIBuilder::getBaseClassArray(SmallVectorImpl<MSRTTIClass> &Classes) {
3776  SmallString<256> MangledName;
3777  {
3778  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(MangledName);
3779  ABI.getMangleContext().mangleCXXRTTIBaseClassArray(RD, Out);
3780  }
3781 
3782  // Forward-declare the base class array.
3783  // cl.exe pads the base class array with 1 (in 32 bit mode) or 4 (in 64 bit
3784  // mode) bytes of padding. We provide a pointer sized amount of padding by
3785  // adding +1 to Classes.size(). The sections have pointer alignment and are

3799  for (MSRTTIClass &Class : Classes)
3800  BaseClassArrayData.push_back(
3801  ABI.getImageRelativeConstant(getBaseClassDescriptor(Class)));
3802  BaseClassArrayData.push_back(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(PtrType));
3803  BCA->setInitializer(llvm::ConstantArray::get(ArrType, BaseClassArrayData));
3804  return BCA;

3832  auto Type = ABI.getBaseClassDescriptorType();

3834  new llvm::GlobalVariable(Module, Type, /*isConstant=*/true, Linkage,

3902 static QualType decomposeTypeForEH(ASTContext &Context, QualType T,
3903  bool &IsConst, bool &IsVolatile,
3904  bool &IsUnaligned) {
3905  T = Context.getExceptionObjectType(T);
3906 
3907  // C++14 [except.handle]p3:
3908  // A handler is a match for an exception object of type E if [...]
3909  // - the handler is of type cv T or const T& where T is a pointer type and
3910  // E is a pointer type that can be converted to T by [...]
3911  // - a qualification conversion
3912  IsConst = false;
3913  IsVolatile = false;
3914  IsUnaligned = false;
3915  QualType PointeeType = T->getPointeeType();
3916  if (!PointeeType.isNull()) {
3917  IsConst = PointeeType.isConstQualified();
3918  IsVolatile = PointeeType.isVolatileQualified();
3919  IsUnaligned = PointeeType.getQualifiers().hasUnaligned();
3920  }
3921 
3922  // Member pointer types like "const int A::*" are represented by having RTTI
3923  // for "int A::*" and separately storing the const qualifier.
3924  if (const auto *MPTy = T->getAs<MemberPointerType>())
3925  T = Context.getMemberPointerType(PointeeType.getUnqualifiedType(),
3926  MPTy->getClass());
3927 
3928  // Pointer types like "const int * const *" are represented by having RTTI
3929  // for "const int **" and separately storing the const qualifier.
3930  if (T->isPointerType())
3931  T = Context.getPointerType(PointeeType.getUnqualifiedType());
3932 
3933  return T;
3934 }

3936 CatchTypeInfo
3937 MicrosoftCXXABI::getAddrOfCXXCatchHandlerType(QualType Type,
3938  QualType CatchHandlerType) {
3939  // TypeDescriptors for exceptions never have qualified pointer types,
3940  // qualifiers are stored separately in order to support qualification
3941  // conversions.
3942  bool IsConst, IsVolatile, IsUnaligned;
3943  Type =
3944  decomposeTypeForEH(getContext(), Type, IsConst, IsVolatile, IsUnaligned);
3945 
3946  bool IsReference = CatchHandlerType->isReferenceType();
3947 
3948  uint32_t Flags = 0;
3949  if (IsConst)
3950  Flags |= 1;
3951  if (IsVolatile)
3952  Flags |= 2;
3953  if (IsUnaligned)
3954  Flags |= 4;
3955  if (IsReference)
3956  Flags |= 8;
3957 
3958  return CatchTypeInfo{getAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(Type)->stripPointerCasts(),
3959  Flags};
3960 }

4011 void MicrosoftCXXABI::emitCXXStructor(GlobalDecl GD) {
4012  if (auto *ctor = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(GD.getDecl())) {
4013  // There are no constructor variants, always emit the complete destructor.
4014  llvm::Function *Fn =
4015  CGM.codegenCXXStructor(GD.getWithCtorType(Ctor_Complete));
4016  CGM.maybeSetTrivialComdat(*ctor, *Fn);
4017  return;
4018  }
4019 
4020  auto *dtor = cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(GD.getDecl());
4021 
4022  // Emit the base destructor if the base and complete (vbase) destructors are
4023  // equivalent. This effectively implements -mconstructor-aliases as part of
4024  // the ABI.
4025  if (GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Complete &&
4026  dtor->getParent()->getNumVBases() == 0)
4027  GD = GD.getWithDtorType(Dtor_Base);
4028 
4029  // The base destructor is equivalent to the base destructor of its
4030  // base class if there is exactly one non-virtual base class with a
4031  // non-trivial destructor, there are no fields with a non-trivial
4032  // destructor, and the body of the destructor is trivial.
4033  if (GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Base && !CGM.TryEmitBaseDestructorAsAlias(dtor))
4034  return;
4035 
4036  llvm::Function *Fn = CGM.codegenCXXStructor(GD);
4037  if (Fn->isWeakForLinker())
4038  Fn->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(Fn->getName()));
4039 }

4041 llvm::Function *
4042 MicrosoftCXXABI::getAddrOfCXXCtorClosure(const CXXConstructorDecl *CD,
4043  CXXCtorType CT) {
4044  assert(CT == Ctor_CopyingClosure || CT == Ctor_DefaultClosure);
4045 
4046  // Calculate the mangled name.
4047  SmallString<256> ThunkName;
4048  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(ThunkName);
4049  getMangleContext().mangleName(GlobalDecl(CD, CT), Out);
4050 
4051  // If the thunk has been generated previously, just return it.
4052  if (llvm::GlobalValue *GV = CGM.getModule().getNamedValue(ThunkName))
4053  return cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
4054 
4055  // Create the llvm::Function.
4056  const CGFunctionInfo &FnInfo = CGM.getTypes().arrangeMSCtorClosure(CD, CT);
4057  llvm::FunctionType *ThunkTy = CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(FnInfo);
4058  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = CD->getParent();
4059  QualType RecordTy = getContext().getRecordType(RD);
4060  llvm::Function *ThunkFn = llvm::Function::Create(
4061  ThunkTy, getLinkageForRTTI(RecordTy), ThunkName.str(), &CGM.getModule());
4062  ThunkFn->setCallingConv(static_cast<llvm::CallingConv::ID>(
4063  FnInfo.getEffectiveCallingConvention()));
4064  if (ThunkFn->isWeakForLinker())
4065  ThunkFn->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(ThunkFn->getName()));
4066  bool IsCopy = CT == Ctor_CopyingClosure;
4067 
4068  // Start codegen.
4069  CodeGenFunction CGF(CGM);
4070  CGF.CurGD = GlobalDecl(CD, Ctor_Complete);
4071 
4072  // Build FunctionArgs.
4073  FunctionArgList FunctionArgs;
4074 
4075  // A constructor always starts with a 'this' pointer as its first argument.
4076  buildThisParam(CGF, FunctionArgs);
4077 
4078  // Following the 'this' pointer is a reference to the source object that we
4079  // are copying from.
4080  ImplicitParamDecl SrcParam(
4081  getContext(), /*DC=*/nullptr, SourceLocation(),
4082  &getContext().Idents.get("src"),
4083  getContext().getLValueReferenceType(RecordTy,
4084  /*SpelledAsLValue=*/true),
4085  ImplicitParamKind::Other);
4086  if (IsCopy)
4087  FunctionArgs.push_back(&SrcParam);
4088 
4089  // Constructors for classes which utilize virtual bases have an additional
4090  // parameter which indicates whether or not it is being delegated to by a more
4091  // derived constructor.
4092  ImplicitParamDecl IsMostDerived(getContext(), /*DC=*/nullptr,
4093  SourceLocation(),
4094  &getContext().Idents.get("is_most_derived"),
4095  getContext().IntTy, ImplicitParamKind::Other);
4096  // Only add the parameter to the list if the class has virtual bases.
4097  if (RD->getNumVBases() > 0)
4098  FunctionArgs.push_back(&IsMostDerived);
4099 
4100  // Start defining the function.
4101  auto NL = ApplyDebugLocation::CreateEmpty(CGF);
4102  CGF.StartFunction(GlobalDecl(), FnInfo.getReturnType(), ThunkFn, FnInfo,
4103  FunctionArgs, CD->getLocation(), SourceLocation());
4104  // Create a scope with an artificial location for the body of this function.
4105  auto AL = ApplyDebugLocation::CreateArtificial(CGF);
4106  setCXXABIThisValue(CGF, loadIncomingCXXThis(CGF));
4107  llvm::Value *This = getThisValue(CGF);
4108 
4109  llvm::Value *SrcVal =
4110  IsCopy ? CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&SrcParam), "src")
4111  : nullptr;
4112 
4113  CallArgList Args;
4114 
4115  // Push the this ptr.
4116  Args.add(RValue::get(This), CD->getThisType());
4117 
4118  // Push the src ptr.
4119  if (SrcVal)
4120  Args.add(RValue::get(SrcVal), SrcParam.getType());
4121 
4122  // Add the rest of the default arguments.
4123  SmallVector<const Stmt *, 4> ArgVec;
4124  ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *> params = CD->parameters().drop_front(IsCopy ? 1 : 0);
4125  for (const ParmVarDecl *PD : params) {
4126  assert(PD->hasDefaultArg() && "ctor closure lacks default args");
4127  ArgVec.push_back(PD->getDefaultArg());
4128  }
4129 
4130  CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope Cleanups(CGF);
4131 
4132  const auto *FPT = CD->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
4133  CGF.EmitCallArgs(Args, FPT, llvm::ArrayRef(ArgVec), CD, IsCopy ? 1 : 0);
4134 
4135  // Insert any ABI-specific implicit constructor arguments.
4136  AddedStructorArgCounts ExtraArgs =
4137  addImplicitConstructorArgs(CGF, CD, Ctor_Complete,
4138  /*ForVirtualBase=*/false,
4139  /*Delegating=*/false, Args);
4140  // Call the destructor with our arguments.
4141  llvm::Constant *CalleePtr =
4142  CGM.getAddrOfCXXStructor(GlobalDecl(CD, Ctor_Complete));
4143  CGCallee Callee =
4144  CGCallee::forDirect(CalleePtr, GlobalDecl(CD, Ctor_Complete));
4145  const CGFunctionInfo &CalleeInfo = CGM.getTypes().arrangeCXXConstructorCall(
4146  Args, CD, Ctor_Complete, ExtraArgs.Prefix, ExtraArgs.Suffix);
4147  CGF.EmitCall(CalleeInfo, Callee, ReturnValueSlot(), Args);
4148 
4149  Cleanups.ForceCleanup();
4150 
4151  // Emit the ret instruction, remove any temporary instructions created for the
4152  // aid of CodeGen.
4153  CGF.FinishFunction(SourceLocation());
4154 
4155  return ThunkFn;
4156 }

4158 llvm::Constant *MicrosoftCXXABI::getCatchableType(QualType T,
4159  uint32_t NVOffset,
4160  int32_t VBPtrOffset,
4161  uint32_t VBIndex) {
4162  assert(!T->isReferenceType());
4163 
4164  CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
4165  const CXXConstructorDecl *CD =
4166  RD ? CGM.getContext().getCopyConstructorForExceptionObject(RD) : nullptr;
4167  CXXCtorType CT = Ctor_Complete;
4168  if (CD)
4169  if (!hasDefaultCXXMethodCC(getContext(), CD) || CD->getNumParams() != 1)
4170  CT = Ctor_CopyingClosure;
4171 
4172  uint32_t Size = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(T).getQuantity();
4173  SmallString<256> MangledName;
4174  {
4175  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(MangledName);
4176  getMangleContext().mangleCXXCatchableType(T, CD, CT, Size, NVOffset,
4177  VBPtrOffset, VBIndex, Out);
4178  }
4179  if (llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = CGM.getModule().getNamedGlobal(MangledName))
4180  return getImageRelativeConstant(GV);
4181 
4182  // The TypeDescriptor is used by the runtime to determine if a catch handler
4183  // is appropriate for the exception object.
4184  llvm::Constant *TD = getImageRelativeConstant(getAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(T));
4185 
4186  // The runtime is responsible for calling the copy constructor if the
4187  // exception is caught by value.
4188  llvm::Constant *CopyCtor;
4189  if (CD) {
4190  if (CT == Ctor_CopyingClosure)
4191  CopyCtor = getAddrOfCXXCtorClosure(CD, Ctor_CopyingClosure);
4192  else
4193  CopyCtor = CGM.getAddrOfCXXStructor(GlobalDecl(CD, Ctor_Complete));
4194  } else {
4195  CopyCtor = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.Int8PtrTy);
4196  }
4197  CopyCtor = getImageRelativeConstant(CopyCtor);
4198 
4199  bool IsScalar = !RD;
4200  bool HasVirtualBases = false;
4201  bool IsStdBadAlloc = false; // std::bad_alloc is special for some reason.
4202  QualType PointeeType = T;
4203  if (T->isPointerType())
4204  PointeeType = T->getPointeeType();
4205  if (const CXXRecordDecl *RD = PointeeType->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
4206  HasVirtualBases = RD->getNumVBases() > 0;
4207  if (IdentifierInfo *II = RD->getIdentifier())
4208  IsStdBadAlloc = II->isStr("bad_alloc") && RD->isInStdNamespace();
4209  }
4210 
4211  // Encode the relevant CatchableType properties into the Flags bitfield.
4212  // FIXME: Figure out how bits 2 or 8 can get set.
4213  uint32_t Flags = 0;
4214  if (IsScalar)
4215  Flags |= 1;
4216  if (HasVirtualBases)
4217  Flags |= 4;
4218  if (IsStdBadAlloc)
4219  Flags |= 16;
4220 
4221  llvm::Constant *Fields[] = {
4222  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, Flags), // Flags
4223  TD, // TypeDescriptor
4224  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, NVOffset), // NonVirtualAdjustment
4225  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, VBPtrOffset), // OffsetToVBPtr
4226  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, VBIndex), // VBTableIndex
4227  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, Size), // Size
4228  CopyCtor // CopyCtor
4229  };
4230  llvm::StructType *CTType = getCatchableTypeType();
4231  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
4232  CGM.getModule(), CTType, /*isConstant=*/true, getLinkageForRTTI(T),
4233  llvm::ConstantStruct::get(CTType, Fields), MangledName);
4234  GV->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
4235  GV->setSection(".xdata");
4236  if (GV->isWeakForLinker())
4237  GV->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(GV->getName()));
4238  return getImageRelativeConstant(GV);
4239 }

4241 llvm::GlobalVariable *MicrosoftCXXABI::getCatchableTypeArray(QualType T) {
4242  assert(!T->isReferenceType());
4243 
4244  // See if we've already generated a CatchableTypeArray for this type before.
4245  llvm::GlobalVariable *&CTA = CatchableTypeArrays[T];
4246  if (CTA)
4247  return CTA;
4248 
4249  // Ensure that we don't have duplicate entries in our CatchableTypeArray by
4250  // using a SmallSetVector. Duplicates may arise due to virtual bases
4251  // occurring more than once in the hierarchy.
4252  llvm::SmallSetVector<llvm::Constant *, 2> CatchableTypes;
4253 
4254  // C++14 [except.handle]p3:
4255  // A handler is a match for an exception object of type E if [...]
4256  // - the handler is of type cv T or cv T& and T is an unambiguous public
4257  // base class of E, or
4258  // - the handler is of type cv T or const T& where T is a pointer type and
4259  // E is a pointer type that can be converted to T by [...]
4260  // - a standard pointer conversion (4.10) not involving conversions to
4261  // pointers to private or protected or ambiguous classes
4262  const CXXRecordDecl *MostDerivedClass = nullptr;
4263  bool IsPointer = T->isPointerType();
4264  if (IsPointer)
4265  MostDerivedClass = T->getPointeeType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
4266  else
4267  MostDerivedClass = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
4268 
4269  // Collect all the unambiguous public bases of the MostDerivedClass.
4270  if (MostDerivedClass) {
4271  const ASTContext &Context = getContext();
4272  const ASTRecordLayout &MostDerivedLayout =
4273  Context.getASTRecordLayout(MostDerivedClass);
4274  MicrosoftVTableContext &VTableContext = CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext();
4275  SmallVector<MSRTTIClass, 8> Classes;
4276  serializeClassHierarchy(Classes, MostDerivedClass);
4277  Classes.front().initialize(/*Parent=*/nullptr, /*Specifier=*/nullptr);
4278  detectAmbiguousBases(Classes);
4279  for (const MSRTTIClass &Class : Classes) {
4280  // Skip any ambiguous or private bases.
4281  if (Class.Flags &
4282  (MSRTTIClass::IsPrivateOnPath | MSRTTIClass::IsAmbiguous))
4283  continue;
4284  // Write down how to convert from a derived pointer to a base pointer.
4285  uint32_t OffsetInVBTable = 0;
4286  int32_t VBPtrOffset = -1;
4287  if (Class.VirtualRoot) {
4288  OffsetInVBTable =
4289  VTableContext.getVBTableIndex(MostDerivedClass, Class.VirtualRoot)*4;
4290  VBPtrOffset = MostDerivedLayout.getVBPtrOffset().getQuantity();
4291  }
4292 
4293  // Turn our record back into a pointer if the exception object is a
4294  // pointer.
4295  QualType RTTITy = QualType(Class.RD->getTypeForDecl(), 0);
4296  if (IsPointer)
4297  RTTITy = Context.getPointerType(RTTITy);
4298  CatchableTypes.insert(getCatchableType(RTTITy, Class.OffsetInVBase,
4299  VBPtrOffset, OffsetInVBTable));
4300  }
4301  }
4302 
4303  // C++14 [except.handle]p3:
4304  // A handler is a match for an exception object of type E if
4305  // - The handler is of type cv T or cv T& and E and T are the same type
4306  // (ignoring the top-level cv-qualifiers)
4307  CatchableTypes.insert(getCatchableType(T));
4308 
4309  // C++14 [except.handle]p3:
4310  // A handler is a match for an exception object of type E if
4311  // - the handler is of type cv T or const T& where T is a pointer type and
4312  // E is a pointer type that can be converted to T by [...]
4313  // - a standard pointer conversion (4.10) not involving conversions to
4314  // pointers to private or protected or ambiguous classes
4315  //
4316  // C++14 [conv.ptr]p2:
4317  // A prvalue of type "pointer to cv T," where T is an object type, can be
4318  // converted to a prvalue of type "pointer to cv void".
4319  if (IsPointer && T->getPointeeType()->isObjectType())
4320  CatchableTypes.insert(getCatchableType(getContext().VoidPtrTy));
4321 
4322  // C++14 [except.handle]p3:
4323  // A handler is a match for an exception object of type E if [...]
4324  // - the handler is of type cv T or const T& where T is a pointer or
4325  // pointer to member type and E is std::nullptr_t.
4326  //
4327  // We cannot possibly list all possible pointer types here, making this
4328  // implementation incompatible with the standard. However, MSVC includes an
4329  // entry for pointer-to-void in this case. Let's do the same.
4330  if (T->isNullPtrType())
4331  CatchableTypes.insert(getCatchableType(getContext().VoidPtrTy));
4332 
4333  uint32_t NumEntries = CatchableTypes.size();
4334  llvm::Type *CTType =
4335  getImageRelativeType(getCatchableTypeType()->getPointerTo());
4336  llvm::ArrayType *AT = llvm::ArrayType::get(CTType, NumEntries);
4337  llvm::StructType *CTAType = getCatchableTypeArrayType(NumEntries);
4338  llvm::Constant *Fields[] = {
4339  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, NumEntries), // NumEntries
4340  llvm::ConstantArray::get(
4341  AT, llvm::ArrayRef(CatchableTypes.begin(),
4342  CatchableTypes.end())) // CatchableTypes
4343  };
4344  SmallString<256> MangledName;
4345  {
4346  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(MangledName);
4347  getMangleContext().mangleCXXCatchableTypeArray(T, NumEntries, Out);
4348  }
4349  CTA = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
4350  CGM.getModule(), CTAType, /*isConstant=*/true, getLinkageForRTTI(T),
4351  llvm::ConstantStruct::get(CTAType, Fields), MangledName);
4352  CTA->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
4353  CTA->setSection(".xdata");
4354  if (CTA->isWeakForLinker())
4355  CTA->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(CTA->getName()));
4356  return CTA;
4357 }

4359 llvm::GlobalVariable *MicrosoftCXXABI::getThrowInfo(QualType T) {
4360  bool IsConst, IsVolatile, IsUnaligned;
4361  T = decomposeTypeForEH(getContext(), T, IsConst, IsVolatile, IsUnaligned);
4362 
4363  // The CatchableTypeArray enumerates the various (CV-unqualified) types that
4364  // the exception object may be caught as.
4365  llvm::GlobalVariable *CTA = getCatchableTypeArray(T);
4366  // The first field in a CatchableTypeArray is the number of CatchableTypes.
4367  // This is used as a component of the mangled name which means that we need to
4368  // know what it is in order to see if we have previously generated the
4369  // ThrowInfo.
4370  uint32_t NumEntries =
4371  cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(CTA->getInitializer()->getAggregateElement(0U))
4372  ->getLimitedValue();
4373 
4374  SmallString<256> MangledName;
4375  {
4376  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(MangledName);
4377  getMangleContext().mangleCXXThrowInfo(T, IsConst, IsVolatile, IsUnaligned,
4378  NumEntries, Out);
4379  }
4380 
4381  // Reuse a previously generated ThrowInfo if we have generated an appropriate
4382  // one before.
4383  if (llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = CGM.getModule().getNamedGlobal(MangledName))
4384  return GV;
4385 
4386  // The RTTI TypeDescriptor uses an unqualified type but catch clauses must
4387  // be at least as CV qualified. Encode this requirement into the Flags
4388  // bitfield.
4389  uint32_t Flags = 0;
4390  if (IsConst)
4391  Flags |= 1;
4392  if (IsVolatile)
4393  Flags |= 2;
4394  if (IsUnaligned)
4395  Flags |= 4;
4396 
4397  // The cleanup-function (a destructor) must be called when the exception
4398  // object's lifetime ends.
4399  llvm::Constant *CleanupFn = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.Int8PtrTy);
4400  if (const CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
4401  if (CXXDestructorDecl *DtorD = RD->getDestructor())
4402  if (!DtorD->isTrivial())
4403  CleanupFn = CGM.getAddrOfCXXStructor(GlobalDecl(DtorD, Dtor_Complete));
4404  // This is unused as far as we can tell, initialize it to null.
4405  llvm::Constant *ForwardCompat =
4406  getImageRelativeConstant(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGM.Int8PtrTy));
4407  llvm::Constant *PointerToCatchableTypes = getImageRelativeConstant(CTA);
4408  llvm::StructType *TIType = getThrowInfoType();
4409  llvm::Constant *Fields[] = {
4410  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, Flags), // Flags
4411  getImageRelativeConstant(CleanupFn), // CleanupFn
4412  ForwardCompat, // ForwardCompat
4413  PointerToCatchableTypes // CatchableTypeArray
4414  };
4415  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
4416  CGM.getModule(), TIType, /*isConstant=*/true, getLinkageForRTTI(T),
4417  llvm::ConstantStruct::get(TIType, Fields), MangledName.str());
4418  GV->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
4419  GV->setSection(".xdata");
4420  if (GV->isWeakForLinker())
4421  GV->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(GV->getName()));
4422  return GV;
4423 }

4425 void MicrosoftCXXABI::emitThrow(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXThrowExpr *E) {
4426  const Expr *SubExpr = E->getSubExpr();
4427  assert(SubExpr && "SubExpr cannot be null");
4428  QualType ThrowType = SubExpr->getType();
4429  // The exception object lives on the stack and it's address is passed to the
4430  // runtime function.
4431  Address AI = CGF.CreateMemTemp(ThrowType);
4432  CGF.EmitAnyExprToMem(SubExpr, AI, ThrowType.getQualifiers(),
4433  /*IsInit=*/true);
4434 
4435  // The so-called ThrowInfo is used to describe how the exception object may be
4436  // caught.
4437  llvm::GlobalVariable *TI = getThrowInfo(ThrowType);
4438 
4439  // Call into the runtime to throw the exception.
4440  llvm::Value *Args[] = {AI.emitRawPointer(CGF), TI};
4441  CGF.EmitNoreturnRuntimeCallOrInvoke(getThrowFn(), Args);
4442 }

4452 bool MicrosoftCXXABI::isPermittedToBeHomogeneousAggregate(
4453  const CXXRecordDecl *RD) const {
4454  // All aggregates are permitted to be HFA on non-ARM platforms, which mostly
4455  // affects vectorcall on x64/x86.
4456  if (!CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isAArch64())
4457  return true;
4458  // MSVC Windows on Arm64 has its own rules for determining if a type is HFA
4459  // that are inconsistent with the AAPCS64 ABI. The following are our best
4460  // determination of those rules so far, based on observation of MSVC's
4461  // behavior.
4462  if (RD->isEmpty())
4463  return false;
4464  if (RD->isPolymorphic())
4465  return false;
4466  if (RD->hasNonTrivialCopyAssignment())
4467  return false;
4468  if (RD->hasNonTrivialDestructor())
4469  return false;
4470  if (RD->hasNonTrivialDefaultConstructor())
4471  return false;
4472  // These two are somewhat redundant given the caller
4473  // (ABIInfo::isHomogeneousAggregate) checks the bases and fields, but that
4474  // caller doesn't consider empty bases/fields to be non-homogenous, but it
4475  // looks like Microsoft's AArch64 ABI does care about these empty types &
4476  // anything containing/derived from one is non-homogeneous.
4477  // Instead we could add another CXXABI entry point to query this property and
4478  // have ABIInfo::isHomogeneousAggregate use that property.
4479  // I don't think any other of the features listed above could be true of a
4480  // base/field while not true of the outer struct. For example, if you have a
4481  // base/field that has an non-trivial copy assignment/dtor/default ctor, then
4482  // the outer struct's corresponding operation must be non-trivial.
4483  for (const CXXBaseSpecifier &B : RD->bases()) {
4484  if (const CXXRecordDecl *FRD = B.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
4485  if (!isPermittedToBeHomogeneousAggregate(FRD))
4486  return false;
4487  }
4488  }
4489  // empty fields seem to be caught by the ABIInfo::isHomogeneousAggregate
4490  // checking for padding - but maybe there are ways to end up with an empty
4491  // field without padding? Not that I know of, so don't check fields here &
4492  // rely on the padding check.
4493  return true;
4494 }
